1
00:01:07,130 --> 00:01:13,630
RAJ BHAVAN - GOVERNOR'S RESIDENCE

2
00:01:15,255 --> 00:01:16,338
The chief minister is en route

3
00:01:16,421 --> 00:01:17,296
- to the oath-taking ceremony.
- Sir.

4
00:01:17,380 --> 00:01:19,255
- Ensure all arrangements are in order.
- Okay, sir.

5
00:01:19,380 --> 00:01:20,296
- Okay?
- Okay, sir.

6
00:01:39,546 --> 00:01:40,421
Copy, sir.

7
00:01:58,463 --> 00:02:02,046
Every story has a beginning and an end.

8
00:02:02,296 --> 00:02:04,505
But this moment isn't where
our story begins.

9
00:02:04,963 --> 00:02:08,963
To understand where it all started,
we must travel back in time.

10
00:02:15,421 --> 00:02:16,296
Sir.

11
00:02:18,421 --> 00:02:19,588
- Rangaiah.
- Sir.

12
00:02:19,880 --> 00:02:21,380
- Meizu Nayak.
- Sir.

13
00:02:21,463 --> 00:02:22,880
- Ravuthu Nayak.
- Sir.

14
00:02:23,255 --> 00:02:24,463
- Singaiah.
- Sir.

15
00:02:24,880 --> 00:02:26,338
Starting tomorrow,

16
00:02:27,088 --> 00:02:29,505
send your children
to school, not to work.

17
00:02:29,671 --> 00:02:32,671
When they work, we earn.
When they study, we spend.

18
00:02:32,963 --> 00:02:34,130
Don't burden us with this.

19
00:02:35,296 --> 00:02:38,546
I'll pay out of my own pocket
if all 20 children enroll.

20
00:02:39,588 --> 00:02:40,546
Listen to me!

21
00:02:41,046 --> 00:02:43,963
Please, send your children to school.

22
00:02:45,921 --> 00:02:48,046
He's not like the others, man.

23
00:02:48,171 --> 00:02:49,671
He never married and never had children.

24
00:02:49,796 --> 00:02:52,338
He's dedicating his life
and earnings to people like us.

25
00:02:52,588 --> 00:02:54,880
- Shiva.
- May we know who you are, sir?

26
00:02:55,130 --> 00:02:56,796
He's the new headmaster.
He was just transferred here.

27
00:02:58,088 --> 00:03:03,921
BLACK FOREST

28
00:03:07,338 --> 00:03:08,338
- From here.
- Yes, coming.

29
00:03:09,546 --> 00:03:11,921
Two tusks! We've hit the jackpot!

30
00:03:18,088 --> 00:03:19,838
Hey! Over here. Pass it to me!

31
00:03:20,255 --> 00:03:22,963
- These tusks will fetch a fortune.
- Yes, dude!

32
00:03:23,255 --> 00:03:24,630
We're taking these tusks home
no matter what!

33
00:03:24,713 --> 00:03:25,588
Hey!

34
00:03:25,838 --> 00:03:26,713
Hey!

35
00:03:27,046 --> 00:03:28,005
Who is that?

36
00:03:34,505 --> 00:03:37,171
Hey idiots!
Are you out of your minds?

37
00:03:39,713 --> 00:03:40,713
Come on, guys.

38
00:03:43,505 --> 00:03:44,463
Wrap it with the rope!

39
00:05:08,463 --> 00:05:09,380
Thank you.

40
00:05:09,838 --> 00:05:10,880
You came at just the right time.

41
00:05:11,421 --> 00:05:12,463
Where are you from?

42
00:05:12,588 --> 00:05:15,796
- The neighboring Lingaiah Gudem, sir.
- Oh! Is that so?

43
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:17,171
ANDHRA PRADESH TRIBAL WELFARE
RESIDENTIAL HOSTEL

44
00:05:17,630 --> 00:05:18,546
Your name?

45
00:05:19,921 --> 00:05:22,630
Nobody knows his real name, sir.
We all call him Chinnaiah.

46
00:05:22,880 --> 00:05:25,171
- What about his parents?
- His mother died giving birth.

47
00:05:25,463 --> 00:05:26,796
His father, Chenchu Ramaiah,

48
00:05:27,338 --> 00:05:29,046
was a traditional healer
who spent his days in the forest.

49
00:05:29,338 --> 00:05:30,921
He passed away recently too.

50
00:05:31,213 --> 00:05:34,505
The boy scrapes by doing odd jobs
just to keep himself fed, sir.

51
00:05:37,713 --> 00:05:39,296
List me as his guardian.

52
00:05:39,630 --> 00:05:41,463
I'll take care of him
from this day forward.

53
00:05:42,130 --> 00:05:43,005
Okay, sir.

54
00:05:43,088 --> 00:05:45,296
CHINNAIAH - LINGAIAH GUDEM
CHANDRA SEKHAR RAO - GUARDIAN

55
00:05:45,380 --> 00:05:47,213
- Everyone, form a line.
- Come, dear.

56
00:05:47,296 --> 00:05:48,296
Thank you, ma'am.

57
00:05:50,130 --> 00:05:51,421
- Come on.
- Thank you, ma'am.

58
00:05:52,213 --> 00:05:53,088
Thank you, ma'am.

59
00:05:54,171 --> 00:05:55,130
- Thank you, ma'am.
- Here.

60
00:05:56,171 --> 00:05:57,046
Thank you, ma'am.

61
00:05:58,046 --> 00:05:58,963
Thank you, Mom.

62
00:06:06,296 --> 00:06:07,213
Come!

63
00:06:15,463 --> 00:06:16,338
Come on.

64
00:06:16,671 --> 00:06:18,296
- Long live!
- The revolution!

65
00:06:18,380 --> 00:06:20,005
- Long live!
- The revolution!

66
00:06:20,088 --> 00:06:23,921
BHAGAT SINGH

67
00:06:30,755 --> 00:06:32,671
Don't you know it's wrong
to hit the hostel warden?

68
00:06:32,963 --> 00:06:34,630
He was in the wrong, so I hit him.

69
00:06:35,171 --> 00:06:36,046
What did he do?

70
00:06:41,171 --> 00:06:42,088
What's this?

71
00:06:42,546 --> 00:06:44,463
You've been cooking extra rice every day.

72
00:06:44,838 --> 00:06:46,588
Is your illicit lover going to pay for it?

73
00:06:46,713 --> 00:06:47,880
Why would you say that, sir?

74
00:06:48,380 --> 00:06:49,546
These children are growing up.

75
00:06:50,046 --> 00:06:52,213
- They get hungry, so I make more--
- Cut the nonsense!

76
00:06:53,046 --> 00:06:55,088
I'll kill you. You better watch it!

77
00:07:03,671 --> 00:07:06,255
Chinnaiah, stop! Listen to me!

78
00:07:06,421 --> 00:07:07,463
No.

79
00:07:14,505 --> 00:07:16,880
You expect me to be scared
of this little boy?

80
00:07:16,963 --> 00:07:19,296
What are you going to do? Hit me?

81
00:07:45,755 --> 00:07:48,380
Sir, I recently read that
when there's a strong leader in place,

82
00:07:48,463 --> 00:07:50,171
everyone beneath them
works with discipline.

83
00:07:50,588 --> 00:07:52,130
I shared that with him.

84
00:07:52,630 --> 00:07:54,171
And he hit me for it.

85
00:07:54,546 --> 00:07:55,421
He's lying--

86
00:07:57,588 --> 00:08:00,880
The Constitution says
self-defense is a fundamental right.

87
00:08:02,671 --> 00:08:05,463
The Bhagavad Gita teaches us
to stand against unrighteousness.

88
00:08:07,755 --> 00:08:10,630
My conscience urged me
to rise against injustice.

89
00:08:11,046 --> 00:08:12,130
So I hit him, sir.

90
00:08:14,963 --> 00:08:16,005
Self-defense.

91
00:08:16,296 --> 00:08:17,296
Conscience.

92
00:08:18,005 --> 00:08:20,005
These aren't words
that come from a child's mouth.

93
00:08:21,838 --> 00:08:24,671
Someone's been doing their reading, huh?

94
00:08:27,005 --> 00:08:27,880
Very well.

95
00:08:27,963 --> 00:08:29,713
What's this, sir? After all of this,
you're still not taking action?

96
00:08:30,171 --> 00:08:31,421
Oh, I will.

97
00:08:32,088 --> 00:08:33,046
But it'll be on you.

98
00:08:38,921 --> 00:08:42,880
If he's picking fights at this age,
he'll go after big shots when he grows up.

99
00:08:43,421 --> 00:08:44,296
Without a doubt.

100
00:08:46,755 --> 00:08:48,380
You spoke about what makes a great leader.

101
00:08:48,880 --> 00:08:50,505
So tell me... who's your favorite?

102
00:08:50,713 --> 00:08:52,505
I admire Bhagat Singh's fire, sir.

103
00:08:52,588 --> 00:08:55,130
And what about Gandhiji's patience?
Didn't you read about that?

104
00:08:55,588 --> 00:08:57,130
I deeply respect Gandhiji, sir.

105
00:08:57,213 --> 00:08:58,796
But for me,
Bhagat Singh means everything.

106
00:08:59,505 --> 00:09:02,005
Bhagat Singh's fire burns strong in you.

107
00:09:02,255 --> 00:09:04,880
Chinnaiah doesn't suit you anymore.

108
00:09:05,380 --> 00:09:07,505
From this day, your name is Bhagat Singh.

109
00:09:07,838 --> 00:09:08,713
Thank you, sir.

110
00:09:08,796 --> 00:09:10,963
Sir, back when my father
used to heal people,

111
00:09:11,046 --> 00:09:13,088
everyone called him Ustaad. So--

112
00:09:13,171 --> 00:09:16,171
Then, your name is Ustaad Bhagat Singh.

113
00:09:16,421 --> 00:09:18,880
- Ustaad?!
- Thank you so much, sir.

114
00:09:18,963 --> 00:09:19,963
I'm very happy, sir.

115
00:09:20,880 --> 00:09:23,963
If he keeps fighting like this,
how will he focus on his studies?

116
00:09:24,546 --> 00:09:27,171
That boy isn't here to score marks.

117
00:09:27,505 --> 00:09:29,046
He's here to spark flames in the dark!

118
00:09:29,630 --> 00:09:31,546
Master!

119
00:09:32,296 --> 00:09:34,921
- That's what truly matters.
- Master!

120
00:09:35,338 --> 00:09:37,005
Master!

121
00:09:38,546 --> 00:09:39,421
What happened?

122
00:09:39,505 --> 00:09:43,213
You've won the Best Teacher Award,
a state honor, master!

123
00:09:48,463 --> 00:09:51,630
The chief minister himself
is coming to our village.

124
00:09:51,713 --> 00:09:53,755
He's actually coming!

125
00:09:54,213 --> 00:09:55,880
- Please sit down, master.
- It's all right, sir.

126
00:09:55,963 --> 00:09:56,838
Sit sir!

127
00:09:56,921 --> 00:09:59,213
You are the chief minister,
and sitting beside you...

128
00:09:59,296 --> 00:10:01,546
They said the guru is God,

129
00:10:02,171 --> 00:10:04,505
not the chief minister.

130
00:10:05,005 --> 00:10:05,921
Please sit.

131
00:10:06,463 --> 00:10:07,338
Sir.

132
00:10:07,880 --> 00:10:10,630
You've traveled all this way
just to present a simple award?

133
00:10:10,796 --> 00:10:13,713
I didn't come here
to present any award, master.

134
00:10:14,213 --> 00:10:16,963
I came to invite you to join my party.

135
00:10:17,421 --> 00:10:18,630
Join your party?

136
00:10:19,505 --> 00:10:21,630
When it comes to politics...

137
00:10:22,338 --> 00:10:24,755
Politics already has veterans like you.

138
00:10:25,338 --> 00:10:28,963
The more life teaches us,
the less time we have left, master.

139
00:10:29,463 --> 00:10:31,505
A life of selfless service

140
00:10:31,880 --> 00:10:35,046
shouldn't be confined
to just one village or one school.

141
00:10:35,755 --> 00:10:37,296
There's no pressure, master.

142
00:10:37,463 --> 00:10:40,546
Take your time and make the right choice.

143
00:10:40,838 --> 00:10:41,963
Okay, sir.

144
00:10:50,171 --> 00:10:52,171
Hey, what's the matter, Bhagat?

145
00:10:52,880 --> 00:10:55,713
I never thought you'd abandon me too.

146
00:10:57,630 --> 00:10:58,588
Not just me.

147
00:10:59,005 --> 00:11:01,005
You should come too,
leaving everything behind.

148
00:11:01,880 --> 00:11:05,046
Promise me you'll come
whenever I call for you.

149
00:11:20,630 --> 00:11:24,380
PRESENT DAY

150
00:11:27,255 --> 00:11:29,796
The chief minister attending the wedding...
this is no small thing.

151
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:30,755
- Right?
- Namaste.

152
00:11:30,963 --> 00:11:32,588
Hey! Hold on, guys.

153
00:11:33,046 --> 00:11:36,546
This isn't a political meeting.
It's a family wedding.

154
00:11:36,630 --> 00:11:37,546
Sir!

155
00:11:49,588 --> 00:11:52,046
The CM is in critical condition.

156
00:11:52,130 --> 00:11:53,796
We can't predict what will happen next.

157
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:55,213
Under these circumstances,

158
00:11:55,296 --> 00:11:57,838
Karra Nanaji has been
unanimously appointed

159
00:11:57,963 --> 00:11:59,671
as acting chief minister.

160
00:12:05,255 --> 00:12:06,463
Congratulations, sir.

161
00:12:07,713 --> 00:12:10,505
Taking on the role
of acting chief minister brings me no joy.

162
00:12:10,963 --> 00:12:13,421
My heart goes out
to the Chief Minister in his condition.

163
00:12:13,505 --> 00:12:15,588
But now, our focus must be the people.

164
00:12:16,171 --> 00:12:18,005
The opposition
is already stirring trouble,

165
00:12:18,088 --> 00:12:19,380
questioning what protection
ordinary citizens have

166
00:12:19,463 --> 00:12:21,046
if even the chief minister wasn't safe.

167
00:12:21,213 --> 00:12:23,796
As city commissioner,
you must maintain a round-the-clock vigil.

168
00:12:27,880 --> 00:12:28,796
Come, come. Quick!

169
00:12:52,755 --> 00:12:54,880
Sir, what do you say
about the political killings in the state?

170
00:12:54,963 --> 00:12:56,963
Sir, will you push for a CBI inquiry
in the assembly?

171
00:12:57,046 --> 00:12:58,255
Would you classify this
as an act of terrorism?

172
00:12:58,338 --> 00:13:00,046
- Sir!
- As a politician, what's your next move?

173
00:13:00,130 --> 00:13:01,671
- Sir!
- Necropolitics.

174
00:13:01,755 --> 00:13:02,796
- What does it mean?
- It means

175
00:13:02,880 --> 00:13:05,171
we must never turn the dead
into political pawns.

176
00:13:05,296 --> 00:13:07,171
- Sir!
- Sir!

177
00:13:42,838 --> 00:13:44,505
Yesterday, the priest
said something interesting.

178
00:13:51,838 --> 00:13:54,005
Even though all of your palm lines
are remarkably strong,

179
00:13:54,421 --> 00:13:57,296
this one falls short by half an inch.

180
00:13:57,505 --> 00:13:59,380
And that's why
you're not the chief minister.

181
00:14:11,838 --> 00:14:14,088
So... will I finally become CM?

182
00:14:14,546 --> 00:14:16,630
You will, sir. You will.

183
00:14:17,380 --> 00:14:18,296
You will, sir.

184
00:14:22,171 --> 00:14:24,713
I shed my own blood
to claim that seat of power.

185
00:14:26,546 --> 00:14:28,338
You think I'd hesitate
to spill someone else's?

186
00:14:29,921 --> 00:14:34,505
The chief minister the other day...
that wedding cost him his life.

187
00:14:39,630 --> 00:14:40,546
Forget that.

188
00:14:40,796 --> 00:14:42,546
The man who orchestrated the attack

189
00:14:42,713 --> 00:14:44,963
against the next chief minister,
your father, is...

190
00:14:47,630 --> 00:14:48,588
Quick!

191
00:14:53,421 --> 00:14:57,963
All they see is a "chief minister"
in the acting chief minister.

192
00:14:58,046 --> 00:15:01,963
I suggest you see the threat
that comes with it.

193
00:15:04,463 --> 00:15:06,921
And you? What's your move?

194
00:15:16,171 --> 00:15:17,421
I hope you got the point.

195
00:15:18,505 --> 00:15:21,921
I am CM Nalla Nagappa,
and that stands for...

196
00:15:22,463 --> 00:15:24,421
Chadhala Marri Nalla Nagappa.

197
00:15:35,838 --> 00:15:38,255
I, Chadhala Marri Nalla Nagappa,

198
00:15:38,463 --> 00:15:40,421
do solemnly swear in the name of God

199
00:15:40,588 --> 00:15:44,505
to uphold the sovereignty
and the integrity of Bharat,

200
00:15:45,296 --> 00:15:47,963
as the acting chief minister
of Telangana...

201
00:15:48,213 --> 00:15:49,088
That's me.

202
00:15:49,171 --> 00:15:51,630
without fear or favor,
affection or ill will.

203
00:15:52,005 --> 00:15:54,963
I promise to honor my oath.

204
00:16:03,838 --> 00:16:05,130
This victory belongs to every one of you.

205
00:16:05,338 --> 00:16:08,338
It's my father who's the chief minister.
You should congratulate him, too.

206
00:16:08,588 --> 00:16:11,130
Thank you, Dad. Love you!

207
00:16:11,213 --> 00:16:12,421
Love you, uncle!

208
00:16:12,713 --> 00:16:14,838
A thousand congratulations to the prince!

209
00:16:14,921 --> 00:16:18,171
Your father becoming chief minister
means you've become one too, in our eyes.

210
00:16:18,255 --> 00:16:19,463
Cut the extra drama!

211
00:16:19,588 --> 00:16:22,296
It's been five years
feeling like I'm just an extra.

212
00:16:22,421 --> 00:16:25,380
At least introduce us
to your father, Prince.

213
00:16:25,463 --> 00:16:27,463
I'll think about it.
I'm in full party mode.

214
00:16:27,713 --> 00:16:28,755
I'll call you back.

215
00:16:28,838 --> 00:16:30,630
That's exactly why I'm calling.

216
00:16:30,755 --> 00:16:33,630
Why does it always
have to be city parties?

217
00:16:33,796 --> 00:16:35,796
It's all plastic glasses and fake people!

218
00:16:35,880 --> 00:16:37,046
Come out to us, just once.

219
00:16:37,463 --> 00:16:39,671
Mornings drenched in open green,

220
00:16:39,838 --> 00:16:42,380
and nights wrapped in cozy feel,

221
00:16:43,296 --> 00:16:44,630
you'll love every second of it.

222
00:16:45,588 --> 00:16:49,088
Guys! He's talking about the wildest party
in the middle of the forest.

223
00:16:49,171 --> 00:16:50,046
Are you ready?

224
00:16:50,171 --> 00:16:51,546
Yes!

225
00:16:51,630 --> 00:16:53,130
Alright, I'm bringing my friends along.

226
00:16:53,296 --> 00:16:56,838
- Arrangements must be absolutely grand.
- Oh God, once you come out here,

227
00:16:56,921 --> 00:16:57,921
you'll never want
to set foot in the city again.

228
00:16:58,005 --> 00:16:59,546
You have my word.
So what do you say?

229
00:17:05,463 --> 00:17:09,630
SINGAIAH TIMBER DEPOT
(12KMS FROM NALLAMALA FOREST)

230
00:17:15,171 --> 00:17:17,880
Welcome, Prince!

231
00:17:18,046 --> 00:17:19,713
Welcome!

232
00:17:19,838 --> 00:17:22,588
After so many years,
I can't believe I'm finally seeing you.

233
00:17:22,671 --> 00:17:24,463
Welcome!

234
00:17:24,546 --> 00:17:25,421
Welcome!

235
00:17:25,546 --> 00:17:27,713
Get the welcome drink for our prince!

236
00:17:27,838 --> 00:17:29,088
Enjoy!

237
00:17:29,171 --> 00:17:30,880
Enjoy!

238
00:17:30,963 --> 00:17:32,088
What's this, Mr. Singaiah?

239
00:17:32,171 --> 00:17:34,505
We've come all this way.
And no ganja to enjoy?

240
00:17:36,505 --> 00:17:37,713
That just reminded me!

241
00:17:37,963 --> 00:17:39,213
I've got bad news.

242
00:17:39,338 --> 00:17:41,296
This morning, 25 tons of ganja

243
00:17:41,380 --> 00:17:43,713
from your syndicate
was seized by the police.

244
00:17:44,296 --> 00:17:45,171
That's true, sir.

245
00:17:45,546 --> 00:17:46,421
Sir?

246
00:17:46,838 --> 00:17:48,171
How strange is it?

247
00:17:48,588 --> 00:17:51,130
The government is ours. The power is ours.

248
00:17:51,338 --> 00:17:52,546
But the ganja is theirs!

249
00:17:52,713 --> 00:17:54,630
How are we supposed to live like this?

250
00:17:54,963 --> 00:17:57,755
I called you because
I knew you'd sort this out.

251
00:17:59,546 --> 00:18:00,421
Come on, guys!

252
00:18:00,505 --> 00:18:03,213
The CI behind the seizure...
his name is Kesava Reddy.

253
00:18:04,671 --> 00:18:07,505
THE LITTLE BOY... (YOU KNOW)

254
00:18:08,005 --> 00:18:09,588
- I brought you to the station
- Lock all seized vehicles.

255
00:18:09,671 --> 00:18:10,713
because you're driving me crazy at home.

256
00:18:10,796 --> 00:18:12,505
- You'll get calls from higher-ups.
- There's your dad.

257
00:18:12,671 --> 00:18:14,130
Don't answer them without telling me.

258
00:18:14,213 --> 00:18:15,171
- Okay?
- Okay, sir.

259
00:18:16,130 --> 00:18:17,005
Hey!

260
00:18:17,088 --> 00:18:18,005
- Get their fingerprints too.
- On it, sir.

261
00:18:18,380 --> 00:18:19,255
- Take care of it.
- Okay.

262
00:18:19,338 --> 00:18:20,213
What are you doing here?

263
00:18:20,588 --> 00:18:24,130
- You haven't come home in two days.
- I missed you, Daddy.

264
00:18:24,255 --> 00:18:25,130
I'm sorry, sweetheart.

265
00:18:26,380 --> 00:18:27,921
It's 25 tons of seized ganja.

266
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:30,671
We have to guard it around the clock.

267
00:18:32,338 --> 00:18:34,588
It's already been over 48 hours.

268
00:18:35,213 --> 00:18:36,671
Why put yourself through such a risky job?

269
00:18:37,046 --> 00:18:38,796
You could run
my father's business instead.

270
00:18:38,963 --> 00:18:40,546
I could. But...

271
00:18:41,255 --> 00:18:42,963
money isn't everything.

272
00:18:43,755 --> 00:18:45,046
You also need satisfaction.

273
00:18:45,463 --> 00:18:48,130
- I want both.
- So do we!

274
00:18:59,838 --> 00:19:01,171
My ganja...

275
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:04,630
- And your head.
- Mom!

276
00:19:04,713 --> 00:19:07,046
If a CI wields this much power,

277
00:19:07,463 --> 00:19:09,713
imagine what a
chief minister can do.

278
00:19:10,630 --> 00:19:12,630
Want to find out?

279
00:19:18,755 --> 00:19:19,630
Daddy!

280
00:19:21,380 --> 00:19:22,255
Dear!

281
00:19:25,463 --> 00:19:26,338
Oh no!

282
00:19:44,671 --> 00:19:45,546
Hey!

283
00:19:45,796 --> 00:19:47,963
What you're doing is wrong!

284
00:19:48,255 --> 00:19:49,671
You're right. It is wrong.

285
00:19:50,505 --> 00:19:52,380
It's not your clothes
that need to come off.

286
00:19:55,338 --> 00:19:57,713
- Hey! Hey!
- Mom!

287
00:19:58,338 --> 00:20:00,630
Hey... this is wrong.

288
00:20:00,755 --> 00:20:01,880
- Hey!
- I won't spare you.

289
00:20:03,255 --> 00:20:04,213
What's this, Vicky?

290
00:20:04,588 --> 00:20:07,546
I thought she was only his wife.
Why are all these men after her?

291
00:20:08,130 --> 00:20:09,796
- Hey!
- Mom!

292
00:20:09,880 --> 00:20:12,088
- Let go of her!
- Please, leave her alone!

293
00:20:16,380 --> 00:20:18,338
Stop it! Please!

294
00:20:26,588 --> 00:20:29,255
- Dear God!
- Mom!

295
00:20:30,546 --> 00:20:31,463
Chinnu!

296
00:20:34,380 --> 00:20:35,505
Please spare her.

297
00:20:39,671 --> 00:20:42,713
Whenever dharma falters,

298
00:20:46,546 --> 00:20:48,130
and adharma prevails,

299
00:20:48,213 --> 00:20:49,671
to shield the virtuous,
to vanquish the wicked,

300
00:20:49,755 --> 00:20:51,088
and to restore dharma
to its rightful place,

301
00:20:51,296 --> 00:20:53,963
I manifest Myself in every age.

302
00:20:54,921 --> 00:20:55,963
Chinnu!

303
00:21:26,463 --> 00:21:27,338
Chinnu!

304
00:21:47,838 --> 00:21:50,296
Hey! The blow may take time...

305
00:21:50,546 --> 00:21:51,588
But it never misses its mark.

306
00:22:08,380 --> 00:22:10,171
What you heard earlier
was a line from the Bhagavad Gita.

307
00:22:12,546 --> 00:22:13,921
This is Bhagat's line.

308
00:22:17,005 --> 00:22:18,005
Cross it if you've got the guts.

309
00:22:18,171 --> 00:22:19,880
If you knew who my father is...

310
00:22:19,963 --> 00:22:20,880
I'm not interested.

311
00:22:21,380 --> 00:22:22,338
And I simply don't
have the time.

312
00:22:22,546 --> 00:22:23,421
Hey!

313
00:23:02,088 --> 00:23:02,963
Hey!

314
00:23:03,796 --> 00:23:06,921
You toss around the word "violence"
without knowing its weight.

315
00:23:08,588 --> 00:23:11,088
I'll show you what it means.
What it feels like.

316
00:23:11,171 --> 00:23:13,046
Why violence is necessary. All of it.

317
00:23:30,880 --> 00:23:31,755
Hey!

318
00:24:08,380 --> 00:24:09,880
No! Let's talk this out.

319
00:24:10,213 --> 00:24:11,171
Let's sit and talk.

320
00:24:13,296 --> 00:24:14,213
Come on, let's talk!

321
00:24:15,963 --> 00:24:16,838
Move.

322
00:24:18,088 --> 00:24:19,838
- I said move!
- P-please, just hear me out!

323
00:24:25,671 --> 00:24:26,546
N-no.

324
00:24:26,880 --> 00:24:28,088
No. No violence.

325
00:24:28,505 --> 00:24:29,630
I don't want it either.

326
00:24:30,338 --> 00:24:32,046
I only asked him to move.
He misunderstood.

327
00:24:32,713 --> 00:24:33,880
- N-no.
- He's gone. For good.

328
00:24:41,838 --> 00:24:45,505
Protect dharma,
and it will protect you in return.

329
00:24:45,838 --> 00:24:49,130
- Dharma protects
- Dharma protects

330
00:24:49,213 --> 00:24:51,463
- those who protect it.
- those who protect it.

331
00:24:57,921 --> 00:24:59,255
How's the chief minister doing now, sir?

332
00:25:01,921 --> 00:25:04,046
He's responding well
to his treatment in Singapore.

333
00:25:04,755 --> 00:25:05,963
He'll be back in India soon.

334
00:25:06,463 --> 00:25:08,338
As soon as he's here, go see him.

335
00:25:09,671 --> 00:25:10,921
I need a favor from you, Bhagat.

336
00:25:11,005 --> 00:25:13,463
That's all he ever does these days,
dishing out favors.

337
00:25:14,505 --> 00:25:17,213
No fun, no buzz,
not a moment to spare.

338
00:25:17,296 --> 00:25:19,088
- Katta!
- Alright, I'll shut up.

339
00:25:19,213 --> 00:25:21,380
Madhusudhan Rao.
A prominent industrialist.

340
00:25:21,505 --> 00:25:23,005
He's a close friend
to the finance minister.

341
00:25:23,338 --> 00:25:25,005
His family is coming to the forest resort

342
00:25:25,088 --> 00:25:26,338
for the pre-wedding celebrations
of his younger daughter.

343
00:25:26,921 --> 00:25:29,296
His elder daughter
wants to explore the forest.

344
00:25:29,380 --> 00:25:32,088
Keep her safe until they leave.

345
00:25:32,171 --> 00:25:35,796
- Show her around the forest.
- I'm good with kids, Mr. Rao.

346
00:25:35,963 --> 00:25:37,546
But babysitting a grown woman
is a different matter.

347
00:25:37,630 --> 00:25:38,630
Please, leave me out of this.

348
00:25:38,755 --> 00:25:41,921
You don't get to say no.
Her father is a wealthy industrialist.

349
00:25:42,213 --> 00:25:45,380
If she loves it here,
they will adopt the forest.

350
00:25:45,713 --> 00:25:48,421
You've always had a way of roping me in
under the name of development.

351
00:25:49,046 --> 00:25:49,921
So be it.

352
00:25:50,088 --> 00:25:53,213
When's that "special weather"
hitting the forest?

353
00:25:54,505 --> 00:25:55,421
Tomorrow.

354
00:25:55,963 --> 00:25:56,838
So, please.

355
00:26:11,088 --> 00:26:12,255
- Welcome, sir.
- Smooth journey, I hope?

356
00:26:12,338 --> 00:26:13,880
- Yes.
- Welcome to Mountain Trails Resort, sir.

357
00:26:13,963 --> 00:26:17,046
- What is this, a full family reunion?
- Something about a pre-wedding ceremony.

358
00:26:17,130 --> 00:26:19,463
I've heard of destination weddings,
but a pre-wedding ceremony?

359
00:26:19,546 --> 00:26:21,755
If the wedding is the climax
of a man's life,

360
00:26:21,838 --> 00:26:23,338
the pre-wedding is the pre-climax.

361
00:26:23,505 --> 00:26:25,088
What a good resort. It looks very nice.

362
00:26:25,171 --> 00:26:26,755
I'm Upendra, the resort owner.

363
00:26:27,088 --> 00:26:27,963
And this is Ustaad.

364
00:26:28,046 --> 00:26:29,421
- I'll take care of your stay.
- Namaste.

365
00:26:29,505 --> 00:26:30,546
and he's responsible for your safety.

366
00:26:31,588 --> 00:26:32,463
That's right, Ustaad.

367
00:26:33,130 --> 00:26:35,130
I've heard great things about you.

368
00:26:35,546 --> 00:26:37,130
You'll see far more
than what you've heard.

369
00:26:37,880 --> 00:26:39,713
He's just very fond of me.
You...

370
00:26:40,505 --> 00:26:42,838
- This is my wife, Rajyalakshmi.
- Namaste.

371
00:26:42,921 --> 00:26:44,338
- Namaste.
- My younger daughter, Kriti.

372
00:26:44,421 --> 00:26:45,713
- The bride-to-be.
- Hi.

373
00:26:46,380 --> 00:26:48,171
- My son-in-law, Karthik.
- Hello.

374
00:26:48,755 --> 00:26:50,213
- My son, Raj.
- Hello.

375
00:26:50,296 --> 00:26:51,171
Hello.

376
00:26:51,255 --> 00:26:52,546
My elder daughter, Shloka.

377
00:26:53,380 --> 00:26:54,255
Namaskaram and welcome.

378
00:26:54,338 --> 00:26:55,255
And the elder son-in-law?

379
00:26:58,005 --> 00:27:00,255
- Without the elder daughter's wedding...
- Everyone, please head inside.

380
00:27:02,546 --> 00:27:03,421
Who's this guy?

381
00:27:03,755 --> 00:27:04,755
- Sir...
- Please come.

382
00:27:04,838 --> 00:27:06,671
I've advised against venturing out
of the resort,

383
00:27:06,838 --> 00:27:09,255
but my elder daughter insists on going
deep into the forest for some therapy.

384
00:27:09,338 --> 00:27:11,796
Don't worry, sir.
Her safety is my responsibility.

385
00:27:11,880 --> 00:27:12,755
Thank you!

386
00:27:12,838 --> 00:27:13,713
Right this way, sir.

387
00:27:13,921 --> 00:27:16,796
The forest is the right place for therapy.
Shloka, I'm convinced.

388
00:27:16,880 --> 00:27:19,046
- Of course, doctor.
- I didn't ask for your opinion.

389
00:27:19,171 --> 00:27:20,088
I was just stating mine.

390
00:27:28,005 --> 00:27:30,463
My shoes are Japanese...

391
00:27:35,880 --> 00:27:38,588
Why is she staring into nothing
instead of the forest?

392
00:27:39,380 --> 00:27:40,463
She's going through
a rough phase.

393
00:27:40,921 --> 00:27:41,838
Just got out of a relationship.

394
00:27:42,255 --> 00:27:43,880
We brought her here
for a change of place.

395
00:27:43,963 --> 00:27:45,171
- Who are you, exactly?
- Muthaiah!

396
00:27:46,171 --> 00:27:47,130
Doctor Samanvai.

397
00:27:48,463 --> 00:27:50,171
- He's my guru.
- Psycho... the rapist?!

398
00:27:50,255 --> 00:27:52,213
Hey! Psychotherapist.

399
00:27:52,505 --> 00:27:54,130
Don't split it. It sounds terrible.

400
00:27:56,088 --> 00:27:57,046
Who are you people?

401
00:27:57,338 --> 00:27:58,296
Please step aside.

402
00:27:58,671 --> 00:27:59,671
I need some breathing space.

403
00:27:59,755 --> 00:28:01,046
Sir, please...

404
00:28:01,130 --> 00:28:03,296
There's more here than meets the eye.

405
00:28:04,088 --> 00:28:06,171
Find out what this therapist
has been doing, Katta.

406
00:28:06,380 --> 00:28:07,838
I'll pull her out of this depression.

407
00:28:07,921 --> 00:28:10,005
We'll erase the past
scarred into her heart

408
00:28:10,171 --> 00:28:11,213
and script a new future.

409
00:28:11,338 --> 00:28:12,213
And finally,

410
00:28:12,296 --> 00:28:14,796
I'll heal the wound with therapy
and replace the hate with love.

411
00:28:15,338 --> 00:28:17,463
If you can do it quickly,
we can all get out of here.

412
00:28:18,380 --> 00:28:19,880
Or we'll bury you here.

413
00:28:23,880 --> 00:28:26,255
Jr. Boss will handle
all the government contracts.

414
00:28:26,588 --> 00:28:28,463
I only handle the payments.

415
00:28:28,671 --> 00:28:31,171
And that too, only when
the jr. boss is fully satisfied.

416
00:28:31,463 --> 00:28:33,755
He'll have absolutely no complaints
about our work, sir.

417
00:28:34,880 --> 00:28:35,838
It's not about the work.

418
00:28:37,463 --> 00:28:38,963
It's about the percentage.

419
00:28:40,505 --> 00:28:43,713
The work and the percentage
must blend like this.

420
00:28:45,296 --> 00:28:48,171
- Currently switched off.
- Switched off! Hey!

421
00:28:48,505 --> 00:28:50,421
- Sir, sir!
- Vicky's phone is switched off.

422
00:28:50,505 --> 00:28:53,088
- Sir.
- Track him down and get him on the line.

423
00:28:53,171 --> 00:28:54,046
Okay, sir.

424
00:28:55,963 --> 00:28:57,880
Where on earth did Vicky go?

425
00:28:58,213 --> 00:29:00,921
What if we get a call
from the CM's office right now?

426
00:29:03,213 --> 00:29:05,588
There are forces out there
that turn your words into reality.

427
00:29:07,255 --> 00:29:10,005
- Hello.
- We're calling from the CM's office.

428
00:29:10,463 --> 00:29:11,880
We've been informed
that Vicky is with you.

429
00:29:11,963 --> 00:29:12,838
Could you put him on the line?

430
00:29:14,046 --> 00:29:15,421
- I won't.
- What?!

431
00:29:15,755 --> 00:29:17,671
He's gone into the forest to have fun.

432
00:29:17,755 --> 00:29:19,005
There's no network coverage out there.

433
00:29:19,130 --> 00:29:21,755
Once he's back in range,
we'll have him call you.

434
00:29:22,171 --> 00:29:25,088
If you'll allow it,
I'd like to speak with the CM directly

435
00:29:25,171 --> 00:29:27,755
and explain everything myself.

436
00:29:30,088 --> 00:29:32,255
Feels like Vicky's about to ruin us.

437
00:29:35,005 --> 00:29:36,213
- That's it!
- Good job, ma'am.

438
00:29:36,296 --> 00:29:37,171
Awesome!

439
00:29:37,588 --> 00:29:40,046
What you're burning down are not photos
but memories.

440
00:29:40,296 --> 00:29:41,213
You're killing it!

441
00:29:42,296 --> 00:29:43,421
Again. Good job, ma'am.

442
00:29:45,130 --> 00:29:46,005
What is this?

443
00:29:46,171 --> 00:29:49,005
Instead of sleeping, you've decided
to set the whole place on fire!

444
00:29:49,421 --> 00:29:50,380
Dr. Samanvai!

445
00:29:52,338 --> 00:29:53,421
This is called fire therapy.

446
00:29:53,546 --> 00:29:54,630
- Hey, Seenu!
- Yes, boss.

447
00:29:54,713 --> 00:29:56,380
The doctor's got a lot of fire in him.

448
00:29:56,463 --> 00:29:57,338
- Yeah.
- What?

449
00:29:57,421 --> 00:29:58,338
Ustaad!

450
00:29:59,380 --> 00:30:00,921
Respect works both ways.

451
00:30:01,380 --> 00:30:02,713
You demand it, but you don't give any.

452
00:30:08,713 --> 00:30:10,088
He's got great timing.

453
00:30:13,213 --> 00:30:14,338
Now this is a joke.

454
00:30:14,463 --> 00:30:16,380
Ustaad! Ustaad!

455
00:30:19,005 --> 00:30:19,880
Call me "Ustaad" one more time.

456
00:30:19,963 --> 00:30:21,755
Please, go on. Ustaad! Ustaad!

457
00:30:21,963 --> 00:30:23,505
Listen to the weight in his voice.

458
00:30:24,671 --> 00:30:25,546
What?

459
00:30:25,630 --> 00:30:28,421
- You think my warning is a joke?
- If it's not a joke, then what is it?

460
00:30:28,630 --> 00:30:31,088
Instead of burning memories,
you should've taught her to light a stove.

461
00:30:31,171 --> 00:30:32,130
Whoever she marries will be a lucky man.

462
00:30:32,213 --> 00:30:35,338
Bloody male chauvinist, stereotypical
old-fashioned thinking!

463
00:30:35,463 --> 00:30:38,630
Why is cooking a woman's job?
Can't men do it?

464
00:30:39,005 --> 00:30:41,963
They should. They have to!

465
00:30:42,130 --> 00:30:44,213
Men were born to cook too.

466
00:30:44,296 --> 00:30:45,713
They just lost their way
somewhere along the line.

467
00:30:46,296 --> 00:30:48,505
We can't keep saying
only mom's cooking is like nectar forever.

468
00:30:48,671 --> 00:30:53,796
I truly hope the day comes
when dad's cooking is worthy of the gods.

469
00:30:53,880 --> 00:30:57,213
We humbly welcome
your empowerment and strength.

470
00:30:57,588 --> 00:30:58,921
Wow, Ustaad! Wow!

471
00:30:59,130 --> 00:31:01,255
- Isn't that a bit much?
- Did you feel the same way?

472
00:31:01,338 --> 00:31:03,213
Shloka, how are you feeling, dear?

473
00:31:03,505 --> 00:31:05,338
Doc... I am feeling very relieved!

474
00:31:05,421 --> 00:31:07,130
Like a weight has lifted.

475
00:31:07,755 --> 00:31:09,255
I think this fire therapy is working.

476
00:31:09,338 --> 00:31:10,796
Hey, it is good to know, Shloka.

477
00:31:10,880 --> 00:31:12,546
- We need to celebrate.
- Ugh!

478
00:31:12,630 --> 00:31:14,463
Will you ever give me a moment's peace?

479
00:31:14,838 --> 00:31:16,755
No matter how hard I try,
you keep digging it up.

480
00:31:16,838 --> 00:31:18,338
You set it on fire,
and I'm the one digging?

481
00:31:18,630 --> 00:31:19,921
- What's this, Katta?
- Ridiculous.

482
00:31:20,005 --> 00:31:22,838
Gopi used to say 'let's celebrate'
for every small moment.

483
00:31:22,921 --> 00:31:24,005
Oh God!

484
00:31:24,130 --> 00:31:26,755
What's with this Gopi?
He left you, but he's haunting me.

485
00:31:27,630 --> 00:31:30,463
Good evening

486
00:31:34,630 --> 00:31:35,505
Brilliant!

487
00:31:35,588 --> 00:31:39,005
Blood running hot
Hungry like a cheetah

488
00:31:39,338 --> 00:31:41,755
Hungry like a cheetah

489
00:31:44,546 --> 00:31:49,255
A fire built on vengeance

490
00:32:05,046 --> 00:32:07,296
Even the pandit is a Power Star fan.

491
00:32:09,963 --> 00:32:11,380
I'm very pleased.

492
00:32:11,630 --> 00:32:14,088
What's going on?
I thought Sangeet night was tomorrow.

493
00:32:14,213 --> 00:32:16,296
Why are they sitting like dead wires?

494
00:32:16,380 --> 00:32:18,171
Forget the wires.
My nerves are about to snap.

495
00:32:18,255 --> 00:32:22,421
We hired a choreographer for the Sangeet
but he ditched us for a film offer.

496
00:32:22,630 --> 00:32:23,713
Why are you telling me all this?

497
00:32:23,880 --> 00:32:25,505
Tell Ustaad and figure something out.

498
00:32:25,630 --> 00:32:28,213
- Or I lose both the payment and the event.
- Means?

499
00:32:28,671 --> 00:32:30,838
Get Ustaad to dance a few steps.

500
00:32:30,921 --> 00:32:33,546
To put Ustaad in the spotlight,
don't drag me into the limelight.

501
00:32:33,671 --> 00:32:34,880
I'll see what I can do.

502
00:32:35,171 --> 00:32:36,046
Thank you, sir.

503
00:32:37,505 --> 00:32:38,380
Boys...

504
00:32:38,463 --> 00:32:39,880
- What should I do now?
- You need to dance.

505
00:32:40,130 --> 00:32:41,255
And you need to get
these people dancing too.

506
00:32:42,338 --> 00:32:44,630
- Above all, we need courage.
- Katta.

507
00:32:46,713 --> 00:32:50,005
If there's one word in Telugu
I truly despise, it's "dance."

508
00:32:50,088 --> 00:32:51,546
"Dance" is an English word,
not Telugu.

509
00:32:52,213 --> 00:32:53,088
Since when?

510
00:32:53,463 --> 00:32:55,005
Forget all that.

511
00:32:55,130 --> 00:32:57,296
Don't go back on your word.
Now get the song started.

512
00:32:57,713 --> 00:32:58,755
- Master!
- Yes.

513
00:32:59,421 --> 00:33:00,296
Okay!

514
00:33:15,171 --> 00:33:16,463
- So? How was it?
- How was what?

515
00:33:16,963 --> 00:33:19,588
A hungry child will think
plain pickle rice is a feast.

516
00:33:19,713 --> 00:33:21,171
But you're serving just plain rice.

517
00:33:21,255 --> 00:33:24,296
Our youth need moves, sir. Real moves!

518
00:33:24,505 --> 00:33:25,505
What is this?

519
00:33:25,755 --> 00:33:28,380
Ten steps from here to there,
ten steps back.

520
00:33:28,463 --> 00:33:31,338
That's twenty already!
Twenty, you hear me?

521
00:33:31,755 --> 00:33:34,046
If I had an Apple Watch,
you'd know exactly how sincere I am.

522
00:33:34,296 --> 00:33:36,671
Fine. One more shot,
for the sake of your honesty.

523
00:33:36,921 --> 00:33:38,505
Sir, play our favorite song.

524
00:33:55,546 --> 00:33:56,546
How's this one, Katta?

525
00:33:56,630 --> 00:33:58,838
That's not a lion on the hunt,
that's a lion taking a leisurely stroll.

526
00:34:00,630 --> 00:34:01,505
Sir!

527
00:34:01,588 --> 00:34:03,880
- Maybe the Guruji song suits him better?
- Hey!

528
00:34:04,213 --> 00:34:05,088
Good Idea!

529
00:34:05,463 --> 00:34:07,921
Mr. Baldy!
Play that famous chair song.

530
00:34:33,588 --> 00:34:34,546
How's this step?

531
00:34:34,630 --> 00:34:35,921
When you do a dance step,

532
00:34:36,046 --> 00:34:38,213
it needs to land with impact,
not float around casually.

533
00:34:38,588 --> 00:34:40,671
- You caught on quick, man.
- Anyone would.

534
00:34:40,755 --> 00:34:41,880
Okay. Okay!

535
00:34:42,296 --> 00:34:44,796
This is your final chance, okay?

536
00:34:45,005 --> 00:34:47,130
Hey, play the megastar's song!

537
00:34:47,296 --> 00:34:49,630
Even a corpse would get up and dance.

538
00:35:15,755 --> 00:35:16,963
Ustaad, come here.

539
00:35:17,505 --> 00:35:18,380
Come here.

540
00:35:18,463 --> 00:35:20,546
What happened?
No movement in that body at all?

541
00:35:20,671 --> 00:35:22,838
- You know what the real problem is?
- Your expectations.

542
00:35:23,213 --> 00:35:25,421
To you, dance is just movement and motion.

543
00:35:25,505 --> 00:35:27,088
To me, it's an emotion.
It's a celebration.

544
00:35:27,505 --> 00:35:30,505
Whether it's a game or a song,
it has to carry something deeper.

545
00:35:30,630 --> 00:35:33,255
But the message here is clear,
you can't dance.

546
00:35:33,338 --> 00:35:34,213
Forget that.

547
00:35:34,296 --> 00:35:36,713
- Want me to move like Hrithik Roshan?
- Please don't!

548
00:35:36,838 --> 00:35:37,921
We'll take it from here.

549
00:35:38,005 --> 00:35:39,171
- Please leave, sir.
- Let's just leave.

550
00:35:39,255 --> 00:35:41,796
You don't know
how to use real talent.

551
00:35:42,130 --> 00:35:43,421
- Hey, Katta.
- Yes, boss?

552
00:35:43,588 --> 00:35:45,463
My legs are killing me.
Come on, give them a massage.

553
00:35:48,213 --> 00:35:49,130
Where is he?

554
00:35:49,421 --> 00:35:50,963
Five days and not a single word.

555
00:35:51,046 --> 00:35:53,046
I'm building an empire for him,

556
00:35:53,130 --> 00:35:55,380
and he's out there
chasing girls and parties.

557
00:35:56,255 --> 00:35:58,713
- Stop staring and do something.
- Sir... I'll try, sir.

558
00:36:00,588 --> 00:36:02,671
I already told you,
there's no network out there.

559
00:36:04,130 --> 00:36:05,755
If there's no network,

560
00:36:06,088 --> 00:36:09,005
take him somewhere with reception
and make sure he calls.

561
00:36:09,713 --> 00:36:11,380
Really? Oh, God!

562
00:36:11,713 --> 00:36:14,088
I don't have the nerve
to lie straight to the CM.

563
00:36:14,505 --> 00:36:16,838
Sir went deep into the forest for ganja.

564
00:36:16,963 --> 00:36:18,296
No one has seen him since.

565
00:36:18,838 --> 00:36:22,838
Why not bring in the task force
or the CRPF and sweep the entire forest?

566
00:36:22,921 --> 00:36:25,755
If it comes to that,
I'll speak to the CM personally.

567
00:36:28,130 --> 00:36:29,713
The line went dead for now.

568
00:36:30,421 --> 00:36:31,463
If something goes wrong tomorrow...

569
00:36:33,338 --> 00:36:34,671
Should we send our forces in, sir?

570
00:36:36,421 --> 00:36:37,588
That won't be necessary. I'll handle it.

571
00:36:38,838 --> 00:36:40,963
But sir, shouldn't we deploy
the CRPF and Greyhounds?

572
00:36:41,380 --> 00:36:42,255
Sir!

573
00:36:42,421 --> 00:36:44,255
No need. I said I'll handle it!

574
00:36:46,630 --> 00:36:47,838
Bhai! Bhai, please.

575
00:36:47,921 --> 00:36:49,630
I made a mistake.
Please forgive me, Bhai.

576
00:36:49,755 --> 00:36:53,755
I let greed get the better of me.
Please forgive me, Bhai.

577
00:36:53,838 --> 00:36:54,713
Bhai...

578
00:36:54,796 --> 00:36:56,630
- Miya Bhai!
- Miya Bhai!

579
00:36:56,713 --> 00:36:58,088
Miya Bhai!

580
00:36:58,880 --> 00:37:01,296
My name is Miya Bhai.

581
00:37:04,588 --> 00:37:05,463
Yes, tell me.

582
00:37:05,671 --> 00:37:07,546
Jr. Boss, who went into
the Nallamala Forest, has gone missing.

583
00:37:08,421 --> 00:37:09,421
It's been five days.

584
00:37:09,671 --> 00:37:10,546
Don't worry.

585
00:37:11,088 --> 00:37:12,213
I'll handle it.

586
00:37:12,630 --> 00:37:16,088
Sending in the CRPF
will get Baghdadi into trouble.

587
00:37:16,796 --> 00:37:18,213
Don't put him in danger.

588
00:37:18,380 --> 00:37:20,088
Your son will come back to you safe.

589
00:37:21,130 --> 00:37:22,963
That's Miya Bhai's word.

590
00:37:27,755 --> 00:37:28,755
Peace be with you.

591
00:37:30,130 --> 00:37:32,213
I need to speak with Afzal Baghdadi.

592
00:37:38,005 --> 00:37:40,880
- Peace be upon you, brothers.
- Allahu Akbar!

593
00:37:40,963 --> 00:37:42,213
Allahu Akbar!

594
00:37:42,921 --> 00:37:44,296
Please forgive me.
Forgive me.

595
00:37:44,463 --> 00:37:46,088
Forgive...
Please forgive me!

596
00:37:46,171 --> 00:37:47,046
Please!

597
00:37:47,130 --> 00:37:50,796
This international journalist
infiltrated us under the guise of jihad

598
00:37:51,755 --> 00:37:53,713
and leaked our footage
to the media.

599
00:37:54,046 --> 00:37:56,213
Sever his head from his body.

600
00:37:58,380 --> 00:38:01,213
- Nara-e-Takbeer!
- Allahu Akbar!

601
00:38:01,380 --> 00:38:02,296
Thank you.

602
00:38:03,088 --> 00:38:05,505
Leave the Jr. Boss issue to me.
I'll handle it personally.

603
00:38:05,838 --> 00:38:07,296
He'll return to you safe.

604
00:38:08,171 --> 00:38:09,130
You have my word.

605
00:38:20,255 --> 00:38:22,796
What happened?
Why the shorts today?

606
00:38:23,505 --> 00:38:25,546
- Is this some kind of shorts therapy?
- We're taking an off today.

607
00:38:25,713 --> 00:38:27,546
- So you only drink half?
- Hey!

608
00:38:28,713 --> 00:38:30,713
Why? Care to join us?

609
00:38:30,796 --> 00:38:34,755
- Drinking alcohol is injurious to health.
- But it brings joy to the heart.

610
00:38:34,838 --> 00:38:36,255
You carry on, sir.
I'll keep them company.

611
00:38:36,338 --> 00:38:38,338
- Come again?
- I'll take care of them!

612
00:38:40,088 --> 00:38:41,088
He's coming wherever we go.

613
00:38:41,171 --> 00:38:43,171
Driving away the peace.
We need to keep an eye out for him.

614
00:38:53,755 --> 00:38:55,463
- What do you want?
- It's beyond you.

615
00:38:55,713 --> 00:38:57,463
- Then let me go.
- That's beyond me.

616
00:38:57,546 --> 00:38:59,921
- My father will kill you.
- That's way beyond him.

617
00:39:00,046 --> 00:39:01,755
Ustaad... Ustaad!

618
00:39:02,005 --> 00:39:03,338
The police are here looking for him.

619
00:39:04,588 --> 00:39:05,838
Keep an eye on him.

620
00:39:05,921 --> 00:39:07,130
I'll deal with them.

621
00:39:09,213 --> 00:39:11,171
Come on, let's share it. Please.

622
00:39:16,796 --> 00:39:17,880
What's going on?

623
00:39:18,380 --> 00:39:20,630
- Why are you here?
- The CM's son is missing, Ustaad.

624
00:39:20,755 --> 00:39:23,130
They want the forest swept clean.
But off the record.

625
00:39:23,213 --> 00:39:26,213
We're exhausted.
We need some rest.

626
00:39:26,588 --> 00:39:28,546
- Finding him won't be easy.
- What?

627
00:39:28,630 --> 00:39:31,296
Locating anyone
in this forest is no small task.

628
00:39:31,380 --> 00:39:32,255
Oh!

629
00:39:32,338 --> 00:39:34,880
- Brother! Brother! Brother.
- Hey!

630
00:39:35,755 --> 00:39:38,380
Brother, how long has it been
since we saw you like this?

631
00:39:38,463 --> 00:39:39,963
- You look stylish!
- Hey, knock it off!

632
00:39:40,130 --> 00:39:42,921
You owning the dance floor
while we drank ourselves silly,

633
00:39:43,005 --> 00:39:44,171
- those were the days.
- Yes!

634
00:39:44,255 --> 00:39:45,713
Those days are long gone.

635
00:39:48,671 --> 00:39:51,046
- Him? Own the dance floor?
- Hey!

636
00:39:51,588 --> 00:39:52,796
Hey, little shrimp!

637
00:39:52,921 --> 00:39:54,630
- What would you know about his moves?
- How dare you?

638
00:39:54,713 --> 00:39:57,713
Dance isn't about the words.
It's about the moves.

639
00:39:57,880 --> 00:39:59,505
Getting him back to form might take time.

640
00:39:59,713 --> 00:40:01,171
But once he does,
he'll wipe the floor with anyone.

641
00:40:01,255 --> 00:40:02,880
- Please don't.
- That's just your wishful thinking.

642
00:40:02,963 --> 00:40:05,796
- Ustaad, they might start a fight.
- Come on! Really?

643
00:40:05,880 --> 00:40:10,088
For world peace, for the good of humanity
you must dance, Ustaad.

644
00:40:10,171 --> 00:40:12,588
- We're not leaving until you dance!
- Brother.

645
00:40:12,671 --> 00:40:16,838
We've been waiting years
just to see those legs dance again.

646
00:40:16,921 --> 00:40:22,088
- Yes, brother! Please dance.
- Just one move, brother.

647
00:40:22,171 --> 00:40:24,630
These kids need a wake-up call, brother.

648
00:40:24,713 --> 00:40:26,546
- Really?
- We've already seen enough.

649
00:40:26,630 --> 00:40:28,546
Okay! Okay. Harmony!

650
00:40:29,380 --> 00:40:31,796
- Yay!
- Harmony!

651
00:40:33,213 --> 00:40:34,088
Two or three notes.

652
00:40:34,171 --> 00:40:37,046
If possible, play four, five,
six, seven, and even eight.

653
00:40:45,380 --> 00:40:49,380
When we're boosted
We rise, then fall

654
00:40:50,255 --> 00:40:52,671
Hey bro, you've chosen lines so great!

655
00:40:52,755 --> 00:40:57,755
But we must stay high
Through life's call

656
00:40:58,921 --> 00:41:00,463
Nail it, bro! Make it big!

657
00:41:00,671 --> 00:41:05,630
No one can bend us
We stand our ground

658
00:41:06,296 --> 00:41:08,088
Oh wow!

659
00:41:08,171 --> 00:41:13,713
Keep our zeal alive
Till victory's found

660
00:41:40,296 --> 00:41:43,130
When we're boosted
We rise, then fall

