698
00:44:49,005 --> 00:44:50,713
- Peace be upon you, bhai!
- Fazal!

699
00:44:51,088 --> 00:44:53,338
- Yes, sir!
- I need you to handle something important.

700
00:44:53,546 --> 00:44:55,755
I've never met you.

701
00:44:55,963 --> 00:44:58,338
But I want to see you
just once before I die.

702
00:44:58,671 --> 00:45:00,338
I need your blessings.

703
00:45:00,421 --> 00:45:01,546
First, take care of this.

704
00:45:02,421 --> 00:45:04,255
Forget seeing me.
I'll come and embrace you myself.

705
00:45:04,630 --> 00:45:08,838
I swear by Allah,
you'll see exactly who Faisal Hussaini is.

706
00:45:09,213 --> 00:45:10,255
May God be your shield.

707
00:45:12,505 --> 00:45:14,963
You were all fire the other day.
Now it's water therapy?

708
00:45:17,088 --> 00:45:19,671
Ma'am, why was your
symphony of sorrow playing all night?

709
00:45:19,755 --> 00:45:20,755
It's a music therapy, sir.

710
00:45:21,130 --> 00:45:22,338
- Our guru invented it.
- Yeah.

711
00:45:22,463 --> 00:45:25,255
Wounds that words cannot heal, songs will.

712
00:45:25,755 --> 00:45:27,088
Dr. Samanvai, you know?

713
00:45:28,088 --> 00:45:29,005
Yeah.

714
00:45:29,630 --> 00:45:31,088
I was singing for myself.

715
00:45:31,546 --> 00:45:33,463
That's perfectly fine,
but some of us need sleep too.

716
00:45:33,963 --> 00:45:35,755
Why must your breakup
serve as our wake-up call?

717
00:45:35,921 --> 00:45:37,505
- Hello!
- If you knew what she'd been through,

718
00:45:37,588 --> 00:45:38,546
you wouldn't speak like that.

719
00:45:38,630 --> 00:45:39,505
Then tell us.

720
00:45:39,796 --> 00:45:41,921
Go on. Share the scars Gopi gave you.

721
00:45:42,005 --> 00:45:43,546
No way! I don't want to dig.

722
00:45:43,838 --> 00:45:45,546
You have to dig, ma'am.
You must go deeper.

723
00:45:46,130 --> 00:45:47,921
Happiness doubles when shared.
And problems, when shared...

724
00:45:48,005 --> 00:45:49,921
- Triple?
- Your face will be crippled!

725
00:45:50,546 --> 00:45:51,588
Problems get cut in half.

726
00:45:53,505 --> 00:45:56,213
- Dr. Samanvai!
- Okay, let's give it a try.

727
00:45:58,546 --> 00:46:00,005
We met on Instagram.

728
00:46:00,463 --> 00:46:01,838
- See this Gopi.
- Yes, nice.

729
00:46:01,921 --> 00:46:04,088
He got close to our family in no time.

730
00:46:04,171 --> 00:46:06,588
Happy birthday to you!

731
00:46:06,921 --> 00:46:10,796
Just when I thought
life with Gopi was everything I hoped for...

732
00:46:10,880 --> 00:46:11,880
He hopped away?

733
00:46:13,546 --> 00:46:16,963
Right under our noses,
within our own family...

734
00:46:17,088 --> 00:46:18,838
Don't tell me he fell for your sister.

735
00:46:18,921 --> 00:46:19,880
Not my sister.

736
00:46:21,046 --> 00:46:22,296
He fell in love with my brother!

737
00:46:24,255 --> 00:46:25,838
Hi, Aunty. How are you?

738
00:46:31,588 --> 00:46:35,380
So Gopi didn't break your heart,
he just broke out of the closet?

739
00:46:35,463 --> 00:46:37,755
Just shut up!
Learn to respect people's feelings.

740
00:46:38,046 --> 00:46:39,671
How can you laugh at something like this?

741
00:46:39,755 --> 00:46:40,630
Forget him.

742
00:46:41,005 --> 00:46:46,130
Ma'am, Gopi leaves and you go to therapy?
You should celebrate instead.

743
00:46:47,713 --> 00:46:49,505
Ma'am, your real problem
isn't the breakup.

744
00:46:49,671 --> 00:46:54,296
It's how society, especially social media
spreads rumors about us.

745
00:46:54,713 --> 00:46:56,046
How can you call your life shattered

746
00:46:56,171 --> 00:46:57,380
when the lens
you're looking through is broken?

747
00:46:57,463 --> 00:46:58,630
Set it aside and really look.

748
00:46:58,713 --> 00:47:01,421
You'll understand,
Life isn't broken. It's the lens.

749
00:47:01,630 --> 00:47:03,380
She doesn't even wear glasses.
What's your problem?

750
00:47:03,505 --> 00:47:06,255
You! You're her broken lens.

751
00:47:06,421 --> 00:47:09,088
For money, you convinced
a perfectly fine woman she was broken.

752
00:47:09,921 --> 00:47:14,505
True happiness isn't about likes,
it's about genuinely loving your life.

753
00:47:15,421 --> 00:47:18,213
The phone should be in our grip.
Not the other way around.

754
00:47:18,796 --> 00:47:19,963
What do you even lack, ma'am?

755
00:47:20,880 --> 00:47:21,838
One look into those eyes,

756
00:47:21,921 --> 00:47:24,046
and even the greatest swimmer
wouldn't make it out alive.

757
00:47:24,546 --> 00:47:26,005
And that nose?

758
00:47:26,380 --> 00:47:27,963
It'll drive straight into the heart
like a chisel.

759
00:47:28,546 --> 00:47:29,630
And as for those lips,

760
00:47:30,255 --> 00:47:34,088
no words could ever do them justice.

761
00:47:34,296 --> 00:47:38,130
So, my dear Shloka, stop crying,
and start loving your life.

762
00:47:40,171 --> 00:47:42,463
Learn to fall in love with your life.

763
00:47:43,213 --> 00:47:46,046
Life is so beautiful!
Life is extraordinary!

764
00:47:46,130 --> 00:47:49,005
Love this forest, this river,
the mountains,

765
00:47:49,088 --> 00:47:50,463
and love everything around you.

766
00:47:50,546 --> 00:47:53,505
Because love... that's all life is about.

767
00:48:20,338 --> 00:48:21,296
Hey!

768
00:48:21,713 --> 00:48:25,380
The sun is blazing right in my face.
Someone hold an umbrella!

769
00:48:29,671 --> 00:48:31,505
Hey girl, life without you...

770
00:48:33,255 --> 00:48:34,213
Is completely upside down

771
00:48:41,130 --> 00:48:42,130
Where is Vicky?

772
00:48:42,213 --> 00:48:45,963
I swear, I am not here
to play games with the CM.

773
00:48:46,046 --> 00:48:51,380
The forest CI seized the ganja.
Vicky went after it and vanished.

774
00:48:55,130 --> 00:48:56,588
Where do I find this CI?

775
00:48:57,338 --> 00:48:59,838
It's been days
since I've had coffee in peace.

776
00:49:00,088 --> 00:49:01,005
Here, take it.

777
00:49:14,546 --> 00:49:15,588
I swear!

778
00:49:15,880 --> 00:49:17,713
When he asked me
to release the seized ganja, I refused.

779
00:49:17,796 --> 00:49:19,796
He left after warning me.

780
00:49:20,213 --> 00:49:21,213
Please, believe me.

781
00:49:21,505 --> 00:49:22,505
Please.

782
00:49:23,546 --> 00:49:26,213
I beg you,
please have mercy on my husband.

783
00:49:26,630 --> 00:49:28,088
If he had done anything wrong,

784
00:49:28,296 --> 00:49:30,338
we wouldn't have
the courage to stand here.

785
00:49:30,921 --> 00:49:33,046
- Please, spare us.
- Please!

786
00:49:33,713 --> 00:49:34,588
Please!

787
00:49:34,671 --> 00:49:35,838
Why are we even afraid of them, Mom?

788
00:49:35,921 --> 00:49:37,588
Just call Ustaad uncle,
he'll deal with them

789
00:49:37,671 --> 00:49:38,838
- just like last time, right?
- Hey, be quiet!

790
00:49:38,963 --> 00:49:39,921
Why are you afraid of them, Dad?

791
00:49:40,005 --> 00:49:41,380
Ustaad?

792
00:49:42,130 --> 00:49:43,171
Who's this Ustaad?

793
00:49:50,588 --> 00:49:52,463
You said this was a forest getaway, right?
Come on, let's go!

794
00:49:53,255 --> 00:49:54,963
We found Ustaad!

795
00:49:55,088 --> 00:49:57,963
He's the one who's been
disrupting my operations in the forest!

796
00:50:04,296 --> 00:50:05,880
Hussaini brother!

797
00:50:06,630 --> 00:50:10,838
Now I know exactly how to play this.
I need to capture the right person.

798
00:50:13,338 --> 00:50:14,755
Finally...

799
00:50:15,421 --> 00:50:16,880
That Ustaad will be here.

800
00:50:17,796 --> 00:50:19,005
Just watch.

801
00:50:24,588 --> 00:50:25,505
Tell me what happened?

802
00:50:27,713 --> 00:50:30,463
Ma'am, we're here to kidnap you.

803
00:50:30,713 --> 00:50:32,171
Please cooperate with us.

804
00:50:32,880 --> 00:50:34,713
Who exactly are you people?

805
00:50:34,921 --> 00:50:37,005
Let's move ahead and break it down.

806
00:50:37,338 --> 00:50:38,963
It seems someone
from their family is with you.

807
00:50:39,338 --> 00:50:41,338
They said they won't release her
unless we hand him over.

808
00:50:43,130 --> 00:50:44,880
You said our safety
was your responsibility.

809
00:50:44,963 --> 00:50:46,421
Don't take this as a demand.

810
00:50:46,755 --> 00:50:48,255
- I'm asking you.
- Please!

811
00:50:48,338 --> 00:50:50,963
Ma'am, when I give my word,
I stake my life on it

812
00:50:52,171 --> 00:50:53,796
and see it through to the end.

813
00:50:55,338 --> 00:50:56,255
Thank you!

814
00:51:30,755 --> 00:51:33,255
- Welcome, sir--
- Beat it, clown face!

815
00:51:37,296 --> 00:51:39,380
Faizal, put Vicky on the line.

816
00:51:39,838 --> 00:51:41,255
Okay, brother.
Please speak with him.

817
00:51:42,296 --> 00:51:44,380
- Uncle!
- Vicky, my boy.

818
00:51:45,005 --> 00:51:45,921
Everything alright?

819
00:51:46,046 --> 00:51:49,171
A blade, Uncle.
You sent someone razor-sharp.

820
00:51:51,046 --> 00:51:53,713
Uncle, I won't rest until I see his end.

821
00:51:56,546 --> 00:52:00,338
- He put me through hell.
- Who is that madman, Vicky?

822
00:52:00,713 --> 00:52:02,296
I honestly can't decide
whether to be furious

823
00:52:02,671 --> 00:52:05,005
or feel sorry for the fool
who dared to go up against you.

824
00:52:05,171 --> 00:52:08,546
Before he dies, I want to see his face.
Turn on the camera.

825
00:52:43,630 --> 00:52:44,588
Bhagat!

826
00:52:48,213 --> 00:52:49,630
Bhagat Singh!

827
00:52:51,213 --> 00:52:52,630
How have you been, Miya Bhai?

828
00:52:53,963 --> 00:52:55,630
Ustaad Bhagat Singh!

829
00:52:56,046 --> 00:52:58,255
This was a mistake! I made a mistake.

830
00:52:58,338 --> 00:53:00,005
I made a mistake, Ustaad bhai!

831
00:53:01,005 --> 00:53:02,963
Ustaad bhai, please forgive me!

832
00:53:03,046 --> 00:53:04,171
It's been so long.

833
00:53:04,255 --> 00:53:05,380
It was a mistake, Ustaad bhai.

834
00:53:05,463 --> 00:53:07,630
- I beg you!
- You remember everything, right?

835
00:53:08,338 --> 00:53:10,171
It was big mistake, Ustaad bhai! Mercy!

836
00:53:10,380 --> 00:53:11,588
I seek your mercy, Ustaad bhai!

837
00:53:11,713 --> 00:53:13,046
Please forgive me, Ustaad bhai!

838
00:53:13,130 --> 00:53:14,588
Please spare the kid,
Ustaad bhai!

839
00:53:19,380 --> 00:53:21,296
I'll make sure
he understands who you are.

840
00:53:27,880 --> 00:53:29,130
Uncle, why are you begging this man?

841
00:53:29,255 --> 00:53:31,296
- Have you lost your mind?
- Shut your mouth, you fool!

842
00:53:31,630 --> 00:53:33,796
If you value your life,
fall at his feet.

843
00:53:33,880 --> 00:53:36,213
- What are you saying?
- Beg for his forgiveness!

844
00:53:36,380 --> 00:53:38,755
- Why are you afraid of him?
- On your knees. Now!

845
00:53:39,630 --> 00:53:41,796
Faizal bhai!
What is uncle going on about?

846
00:53:42,380 --> 00:53:45,255
Uncle, we have Faizal
and every one of our men right here.

847
00:53:45,421 --> 00:53:47,296
What can one man possibly do
against all of us?

848
00:53:48,963 --> 00:53:51,880
Ustaad bhai, please spare the kid
for my sake.

849
00:53:56,921 --> 00:53:58,088
This old geezer has completely lost it.

850
00:53:58,338 --> 00:53:59,796
He won't come to his senses
until we finish him.

851
00:54:16,671 --> 00:54:19,171
Ex-Forest Ranger, Singaiah.
Reporting, sir!

852
00:54:26,921 --> 00:54:28,713
No formalities between us.

853
00:54:28,963 --> 00:54:29,880
Get me some tea.

854
00:54:31,088 --> 00:54:34,838
How dare you point your gun at him,
you scrawny rat?

855
00:54:40,796 --> 00:54:43,838
You thought you came here
to get high and have a good time.

856
00:54:43,921 --> 00:54:48,255
But it was Ustaad who lured you here
under the guise of a party.

857
00:55:04,505 --> 00:55:07,380
You thought these muscle heads
were here to rescue you.

858
00:55:07,463 --> 00:55:10,671
But it was Ustaad who made them come here.

859
00:55:18,755 --> 00:55:21,088
You thought you had outsmarted Ustaad.

860
00:55:21,171 --> 00:55:24,630
Turns out he was ten steps ahead
of every single one of you.

861
00:55:33,088 --> 00:55:33,963
Hey!

862
00:55:34,046 --> 00:55:37,046
A hundred jackals may gather,
but there's only one king of the jungle.

863
00:55:37,171 --> 00:55:38,671
And that lion is standing right here.

864
00:55:46,921 --> 00:55:47,963
Ustaad!

865
00:55:48,463 --> 00:55:50,796
We haven't seen the real you in ages.

866
00:55:50,921 --> 00:55:52,213
Will you show us, just once?

867
00:57:17,796 --> 00:57:18,755
Get up!

868
00:57:25,338 --> 00:57:26,505
Do you understand now?

869
00:57:27,130 --> 00:57:30,171
My groundwork is rock solid,
and my network's next level.

870
00:57:30,963 --> 00:57:32,338
You've got company.

871
00:57:34,630 --> 00:57:35,630
Congrats.

872
00:57:35,921 --> 00:57:37,463
I expected your brother Baghdadi
to come for him.

873
00:57:37,546 --> 00:57:39,005
But you showed up instead.
Makes no difference.

874
00:57:40,505 --> 00:57:41,380
He'll come.

875
00:57:42,338 --> 00:57:44,963
Your brother will be here
and his father won't be far behind.

876
00:57:46,588 --> 00:57:47,505
Get lost!

877
00:58:05,296 --> 00:58:07,421
You'll be back with your family
within 30 minutes.

878
00:58:09,046 --> 00:58:10,255
Let me know if you need anything.

879
00:58:12,463 --> 00:58:13,963
I need answers first.

880
00:58:14,505 --> 00:58:17,130
Why are you after me?
We have no business with each other.

881
00:58:17,296 --> 00:58:19,338
And I have no clue
what your business is with my dad.

882
00:58:20,088 --> 00:58:21,588
Then find out!

883
00:58:23,630 --> 00:58:26,213
After everything that's happened
you still won't tell me the truth?

884
00:58:26,588 --> 00:58:28,130
- That's all beyond you--
- Please!

885
00:58:28,463 --> 00:58:30,296
You don't think I deserve these answers?

886
00:58:30,588 --> 00:58:31,463
I will find out.

887
00:58:31,630 --> 00:58:33,046
- What?
- I'll find out.

888
00:58:36,880 --> 00:58:38,463
It's time you learned about Nalla Seenu.

889
00:58:38,588 --> 00:58:39,463
Your brother.

890
00:58:43,130 --> 00:58:45,255
And you must know Nalla Nagappa.

891
00:58:45,380 --> 00:58:46,380
Your father.

892
00:58:47,838 --> 00:58:50,796
That was the day Bhagat Singh
declared war on Nalla Nagappa.

893
00:58:50,880 --> 00:58:56,005
All hail Lord Lakshmi Narasimha Swamy!

894
00:58:56,671 --> 00:59:01,630
All hail Lord Lakshmi Narasimha Swamy!

895
00:59:08,880 --> 00:59:13,713
All hail Lord Lakshmi Narasimha Swamy!

896
00:59:14,880 --> 00:59:19,630
All hail Lord Lakshmi Narasimha Swamy!

897
00:59:34,088 --> 00:59:36,963
Entering a temple with a shirt on
goes against sacred custom.

898
00:59:37,130 --> 00:59:39,838
A shirt? We'd walk in
even if we were drunk.

899
00:59:40,088 --> 00:59:41,005
Mr. Priest!

900
00:59:44,380 --> 00:59:45,380
You wretched man!

901
00:59:45,588 --> 00:59:48,130
Acts like these
will only bring destruction upon you.

902
00:59:50,171 --> 00:59:51,130
Take it off, man!

903
00:59:55,588 --> 00:59:56,671
You!

904
01:00:26,755 --> 01:00:27,671
Chant!

905
01:00:27,921 --> 01:00:28,963
Try reciting the mantras now!

906
01:00:29,046 --> 01:00:31,755
To protect the righteous...

907
01:00:32,296 --> 01:00:37,005
All hail Lord Lakshmi Narasimha Swamy!

908
01:00:38,171 --> 01:00:43,213
All hail Lord Lakshmi Narasimha Swamy!

909
01:00:48,171 --> 01:00:50,880
To destroy the wicked...

910
01:01:02,380 --> 01:01:05,005
To restore dharma to this world,

911
01:01:08,171 --> 01:01:10,755
I manifest Myself in every age!

912
01:01:13,880 --> 01:01:15,213
My Lord!

913
01:01:15,546 --> 01:01:18,630
I manifest Myself in every age!

914
01:01:54,796 --> 01:01:57,755
Who posted you here at this hour?
Just who the hell are you?

915
01:02:00,671 --> 01:02:02,005
No honorifics?

916
01:02:02,463 --> 01:02:03,421
Really?

917
01:02:04,171 --> 01:02:06,505
I am the bridge
between God and His devotee,

918
01:02:07,005 --> 01:02:08,546
I am the weapon
in the hands of the helpless.

919
01:02:09,546 --> 01:02:11,963
Since I stand in a temple,
I'll state my name and lineage.

920
01:02:12,421 --> 01:02:13,338
Bhagat Singh!

921
01:02:14,171 --> 01:02:15,630
The name is Ustaad Bhagat Singh!

922
01:02:17,088 --> 01:02:18,588
Born of a lineage
that buries its enemies.

923
01:02:19,171 --> 01:02:20,921
And a star that will rip you apart.

924
01:03:22,463 --> 01:03:25,505
Let the chariot procession begin.
Let's see who dares to stop it.

925
01:04:27,921 --> 01:04:29,921
May Lord Vishnu enlighten our minds!

926
01:04:31,171 --> 01:04:33,296
May Lord Vishnu enlighten our minds!

927
01:04:35,546 --> 01:04:37,588
May Lord Vishnu enlighten our minds!

928
01:05:00,255 --> 01:05:03,130
You didn't come this prepared
just to rough up priests.

929
01:05:04,505 --> 01:05:05,921
So what are you really here for?

930
01:05:06,755 --> 01:05:08,130
What's the real story?

931
01:05:09,130 --> 01:05:10,255
Start talking, you numbskull!

932
01:05:10,421 --> 01:05:11,755
- Nagappa!
- What?!

933
01:05:11,963 --> 01:05:13,671
Nalla Nagappa sent us, sir.

934
01:05:15,171 --> 01:05:18,338
He ordered us to spark a riot
because his son didn't get an MLA ticket.

935
01:05:21,296 --> 01:05:22,838
Nalla Nagappa.

936
01:05:25,213 --> 01:05:27,046
Nalla Nagappa.

937
01:05:27,630 --> 01:05:29,630
Interesting name.
Interesting!

938
01:05:35,713 --> 01:05:36,713
Nagappa!

939
01:05:38,088 --> 01:05:39,713
Nagappa! Nagappa!

940
01:05:40,130 --> 01:05:41,046
Nagappa!

941
01:05:41,713 --> 01:05:42,588
Nagappa!

942
01:05:42,713 --> 01:05:44,130
Mind how you say that name.

943
01:05:45,380 --> 01:05:47,421
He doesn't answer to just anyone.

944
01:05:47,713 --> 01:05:49,130
- He won't?
- No.

945
01:05:49,296 --> 01:05:50,171
What if I shoot?

946
01:05:50,921 --> 01:05:52,213
Hey, hey!

947
01:05:52,671 --> 01:05:53,588
Hey!

948
01:05:53,796 --> 01:05:55,421
Sir! Sir!

949
01:05:57,463 --> 01:06:00,338
ACP Bhagat barged in, sir!
He's opening fire on us!

950
01:06:19,463 --> 01:06:20,880
ACP Bhagat!

951
01:06:22,463 --> 01:06:24,880
So you were the one who caused me trouble

952
01:06:25,296 --> 01:06:26,546
at the chariot procession.

953
01:06:28,255 --> 01:06:32,005
So my reputation reached before I did?
I wouldn't have it any other way.

954
01:06:33,046 --> 01:06:35,255
I didn't create trouble. I ended it.

955
01:06:35,338 --> 01:06:37,213
From household staff
to income tax officers,

956
01:06:37,296 --> 01:06:39,088
no one enters without my permission.

957
01:06:39,296 --> 01:06:40,171
How did you get in?

958
01:06:41,713 --> 01:06:43,380
A storm doesn't ask for permission.

959
01:06:43,505 --> 01:06:44,880
An atom bomb doesn't make an appointment

960
01:06:44,963 --> 01:06:46,755
When they strike,
you shut up and sit down.

961
01:06:47,630 --> 01:06:48,880
You have quite a way with words.

962
01:06:49,171 --> 01:06:51,463
You seem well-versed in scriptures.

963
01:06:51,755 --> 01:06:53,421
I'm just as good with guns.

964
01:06:53,505 --> 01:06:54,671
We offer that service too.

965
01:06:56,505 --> 01:06:59,838
You're dismantling the very party
that built you, all for a seat.

966
01:07:01,255 --> 01:07:04,130
Everyone desires power.
Very few are worthy of it.

967
01:07:05,921 --> 01:07:09,130
You may have stopped that riot.
But you will never stop me!

968
01:07:10,171 --> 01:07:12,713
I will become the chief minister.
My son will be an MLA.

969
01:07:13,588 --> 01:07:16,130
I'm already rehearsing
my oath-taking ceremony.

970
01:07:16,880 --> 01:07:19,921
When that day comes,
you're welcome to handle my security.

971
01:07:20,255 --> 01:07:21,130
Now get out.

972
01:07:21,213 --> 01:07:22,463
As long as I draw breath,

973
01:07:22,546 --> 01:07:24,630
neither you nor your son
will ever sit in that chair.

974
01:07:28,713 --> 01:07:32,380
Since this is your first offense,
I came with a warning, not a warrant.

975
01:07:32,755 --> 01:07:34,005
You must be new around here.

976
01:07:34,088 --> 01:07:35,963
New to this place.
Not to this profession.

977
01:07:36,046 --> 01:07:37,713
Do you even know who you're dealing with?

978
01:07:37,796 --> 01:07:39,588
Do you even know who's against you?

979
01:07:40,880 --> 01:07:42,505
This won't end well for you.

980
01:07:42,588 --> 01:07:45,463
If that's what it takes, I'll end anyone.

981
01:07:46,255 --> 01:07:47,255
Who do you think you are?

982
01:07:47,380 --> 01:07:49,671
Just who exactly do you think
you're threatening?!

983
01:07:50,463 --> 01:07:52,463
You expect me to be afraid of you?!

984
01:07:54,005 --> 01:07:55,963
You may be rehearsing your oath.

985
01:07:56,046 --> 01:07:57,921
I'm making one right now.
Listen carefully.

986
01:07:59,171 --> 01:08:01,171
The name is Ustaad Bhagat Singh.

987
01:08:01,796 --> 01:08:06,630
I pledge my absolute and unwavering faith
to the Constitution of this nation.

988
01:08:06,963 --> 01:08:10,671
Anyone who dares violate it,
I will hunt them down.

989
01:08:10,880 --> 01:08:14,880
And anyone who obstructs my duty,
I'll make them regret it.

990
01:08:15,463 --> 01:08:16,796
With God as my witness...

991
01:08:18,671 --> 01:08:19,713
I challenge you.

992
01:08:20,838 --> 01:08:21,796
Challenge?

993
01:08:21,880 --> 01:08:22,921
What challenge?

994
01:08:23,421 --> 01:08:24,421
Never mind that.

995
01:08:24,546 --> 01:08:25,880
But what's with this gesture?

996
01:08:26,296 --> 01:08:27,213
What the hell was that?

997
01:08:27,880 --> 01:08:30,588
When I touch my neck,
it means I've declared war.

998
01:08:35,088 --> 01:08:38,046
I'll be back...
to stop every last crime you commit.

999
01:09:26,755 --> 01:09:33,755
IT STARTS NOW...

1000
01:09:41,338 --> 01:09:43,380
I'll speak to that welfare minister.

1001
01:09:48,463 --> 01:09:50,171
Greetings, sir. How are you?

1002
01:09:51,713 --> 01:09:52,588
Hey!

1003
01:09:53,421 --> 01:09:58,046
A man in uniform never bows
before a politician.

1004
01:09:58,296 --> 01:10:00,588
Whether it's me or anyone else.

1005
01:10:00,838 --> 01:10:02,505
But I'm bowing to my master.

1006
01:10:02,630 --> 01:10:05,130
- Bless me, sir.
- My blessings are always with you.

1007
01:10:05,213 --> 01:10:08,380
Word is you shook the city
like a tsunami the second you arrived.

1008
01:10:09,005 --> 01:10:10,130
I need to speak about that, sir.

1009
01:10:10,255 --> 01:10:13,546
Nagappa set off the earthquake.
I'm just the tsunami that came after.

1010
01:10:13,755 --> 01:10:16,338
- What is Nagappa's problem?
- You are, master.

1011
01:10:16,546 --> 01:10:18,671
- Me?
- You never married.

1012
01:10:19,963 --> 01:10:21,838
Never even thought about
building a life for kids.

1013
01:10:21,921 --> 01:10:25,255
That's why you never let a mistake slide.
You are unforgiving. Always.

1014
01:10:25,880 --> 01:10:28,255
While others grow their fortunes,
you grow your enemies.

1015
01:10:28,338 --> 01:10:30,171
His son has a criminal record.

1016
01:10:30,255 --> 01:10:31,671
That's why I denied him the ticket.

1017
01:10:32,005 --> 01:10:34,005
Most people of questionable character
have a criminal record, sir.

1018
01:10:34,338 --> 01:10:36,755
Nagappa will stop at nothing
for the CM's chair.

1019
01:10:37,296 --> 01:10:38,588
Be careful, sir.

1020
01:10:39,171 --> 01:10:42,588
It would be wise to keep away
from public gatherings for now.

1021
01:10:45,463 --> 01:10:48,255
Those positions were created
to keep leaders connected to the people.

1022
01:10:48,713 --> 01:10:52,046
You said it yourself,
"When the leader stands tall,

1023
01:10:52,213 --> 01:10:53,755
so does the cadre."

1024
01:10:55,046 --> 01:10:56,005
Listen.

1025
01:10:56,213 --> 01:10:57,713
God is on my side.

1026
01:10:57,796 --> 01:11:00,505
And you're right here.
What is there to fear?

1027
01:11:02,755 --> 01:11:03,713
Fair enough!

1028
01:11:09,588 --> 01:11:11,380
Everything's okay.
Sir can come in now.

1029
01:11:13,921 --> 01:11:14,963
What about that case?

1030
01:11:22,963 --> 01:11:26,046
Who had the audacity
to threaten my father under my own roof?

1031
01:11:26,505 --> 01:11:28,421
- I want to know right now!
- Sir!

1032
01:11:30,171 --> 01:11:33,296
You're just a pack of mongrels
sniffing around for bribes.

1033
01:11:33,796 --> 01:11:35,546
Who gave you the nerve
to walk into my home with weapons?

1034
01:11:35,630 --> 01:11:37,130
Who is he? Who the hell is he?!

1035
01:11:37,213 --> 01:11:38,921
- I said, who is he?!
- Sir, just hear me out.

1036
01:11:39,005 --> 01:11:40,463
- Hey, hey!
- Sir.

1037
01:11:40,880 --> 01:11:42,046
Answer me. Who is it?!

1038
01:11:42,130 --> 01:11:43,755
- Tell me!
- Bhagat!

1039
01:11:49,255 --> 01:11:50,296
Bhagat Singh.

1040
01:11:51,338 --> 01:11:55,046
Mahankali Police Station.
Pathar Gunj, Old City.

1041
01:12:16,671 --> 01:12:17,755
Dealing with my dad is one thing.

1042
01:12:18,421 --> 01:12:20,130
Dealing with this Nalla Seenu
is a whole different matter.

1043
01:12:23,963 --> 01:12:25,088
This is what you are.

1044
01:12:26,755 --> 01:12:28,713
With the flick of a finger,

1045
01:12:29,713 --> 01:12:31,713
your entire world shatters.

1046
01:12:39,546 --> 01:12:42,380
Mr. Nalla Seenu, you may be uneducated,
but I respect your ignorance.

1047
01:12:42,963 --> 01:12:46,505
In physics, every material
has its own properties.

1048
01:12:46,588 --> 01:12:49,046
Iron is hard. Just like me.

1049
01:12:49,505 --> 01:12:52,171
Cotton is soft. Just like my heart.

1050
01:12:52,463 --> 01:12:55,421
And the glass...
It's just... Yeah.

1051
01:12:58,046 --> 01:12:59,546
The property of this glass is...

1052
01:13:09,921 --> 01:13:12,338
The more it shatters,
the sharper it becomes.

1053
01:13:15,088 --> 01:13:17,796
- Hey, I'll remember you!
- Brother...

1054
01:13:17,880 --> 01:13:19,546
You better!

1055
01:13:20,713 --> 01:13:22,755
When I said "glass,"
I didn't mean the size. It's an army.

1056
01:13:24,005 --> 01:13:25,421
- An invisible army.
- Hey!

1057
01:13:25,963 --> 01:13:27,921
I'll see your end.
I swear, I'll destroy you.

1058
01:13:28,005 --> 01:13:30,671
- What an idiot!
- Don't forget you have a family!

1059
01:13:30,755 --> 01:13:33,171
- You numbskull!
- Hey...

1060
01:13:33,463 --> 01:13:35,671
- Say "family" again, and I'll shoot you.
- Sir! Sir!

1061
01:13:35,755 --> 01:13:37,338
- Hey, let go of me!
- Sir.

1062
01:13:49,046 --> 01:13:50,713
Sir, sick leave.

1063
01:13:51,255 --> 01:13:53,921
What do you mean, sick leave, Mr. Reddy?
If death comes, face it like a warrior.

1064
01:13:54,005 --> 01:13:54,880
Sir!

1065
01:13:54,963 --> 01:13:58,505
We're organizing a grand Shri Ram Navami
celebration in our street.

1066
01:13:59,630 --> 01:14:00,963
We're looking for donations.

1067
01:14:03,171 --> 01:14:05,671
- The children look adorable. Mr. Reddy?
- Sir.

1068
01:14:06,005 --> 01:14:06,880
Come on, come.

1069
01:14:06,963 --> 01:14:07,880
JAI SHRI RAM

1070
01:14:10,463 --> 01:14:12,963
- Jai Shri Ram!
- Jai Shri Ram!

1071
01:14:13,046 --> 01:14:14,671
- Jai Shri Ram!
- What does it mean?

1072
01:14:15,588 --> 01:14:17,171
It needs no translation.

1073
01:14:17,380 --> 01:14:19,963
If you go hunting for synonyms,
you'll end up saying "Jai Bajrang Bali."

1074
01:14:20,088 --> 01:14:20,963
Oh boy!

1075
01:14:25,296 --> 01:14:26,921
- Yeah, Mujeeb.
- For the past three days,

1076
01:14:27,005 --> 01:14:28,255
there's been unusual movement
in our area.

1077
01:14:28,380 --> 01:14:29,255
What's the matter?

1078
01:14:29,338 --> 01:14:31,171
Unfamiliar faces
have been spotted at Miya Bhai's house.

1079
01:14:34,463 --> 01:14:38,796
Sir, after inquiring,
we identified him as Ajmal Raheem.

1080
01:14:38,880 --> 01:14:40,880
- What name did you just say?
- Ajmal Raheem.

1081
01:14:42,963 --> 01:14:44,296
Ajmal Raheem.

1082
01:14:45,255 --> 01:14:49,380
Ajmal Raheem, a ruthless terrorist
who's haunted this nation since his teens.

1083
01:14:49,588 --> 01:14:51,921
He's not brainwashed like the others.

1084
01:14:52,005 --> 01:14:54,713
He's the mastermind
who brainwashes them.

1085
01:14:55,255 --> 01:14:57,546
Sir, go straight, then take a right.
That's Miya Bhai's haveli.

1086
01:14:57,796 --> 01:14:59,005
- This way? Okay!
- Yes.

1087
01:14:59,088 --> 01:15:01,046
Better remove that tilak, sir.

1088
01:15:01,130 --> 01:15:03,755
I'm heading to the Old City,
not Pakistan.

1089
01:15:46,046 --> 01:15:47,088
Greetings, Miya Bhai.

1090
01:15:51,171 --> 01:15:52,421
I want Ajmal.

1091
01:15:56,213 --> 01:15:58,421
And I want Deepika Padukone.

1092
01:15:58,588 --> 01:15:59,755
Can you bring her for me?

1093
01:16:08,546 --> 01:16:11,296
Send him over respectfully.
Or I'll drag him out myself.

1094
01:16:12,463 --> 01:16:13,838
Cut the nonsense!

1095
01:16:13,921 --> 01:16:16,463
No one dares question us
over an electricity bill,

1096
01:16:16,546 --> 01:16:18,671
and you think you can lay hands
on my guest?

1097
01:16:21,588 --> 01:16:24,005
Bring him down the stairs,
if you've got the guts.

1098
01:16:24,463 --> 01:16:26,046
Get him down.
Let me see you try.

1099
01:16:27,171 --> 01:16:30,755
If he doesn't do it,
I'll strip him and make him dance.

1100
01:16:33,671 --> 01:16:36,963
You walked into our den.
Lower your head and apologize!

1101
01:16:40,963 --> 01:16:43,380
Bow your head, you moron!

1102
01:16:46,880 --> 01:16:50,171
I won't say it again.
Bow your head and apologize!

1103
01:16:53,838 --> 01:16:57,505
Miya Bhai, that won't work on me.
I didn't come this far to bow down,

1104
01:16:57,755 --> 01:16:59,380
I came to take him,
with his head bowed down.

1105
01:17:02,921 --> 01:17:05,755
I'll give you all a chance.
Stop me if you can.

1106
01:17:06,171 --> 01:17:08,171
- Come on!
- Think carefully.

1107
01:17:08,671 --> 01:17:11,380
You're alone. And we...

1108
01:17:11,463 --> 01:17:15,421
Hey, Miya! If I feared mobs,
I wouldn't have walked in alone.

1109
01:17:15,505 --> 01:17:19,463
Before messing with us,
anyone would think twice.

1110
01:17:19,796 --> 01:17:22,796
My issue isn't with your faith, but a man.

1111
01:17:22,880 --> 01:17:24,505
With a man who committed a crime.

1112
01:17:24,963 --> 01:17:27,296
I want his head!

1113
01:17:27,796 --> 01:17:29,171
Right this instant!

1114
01:17:29,255 --> 01:17:32,588
- Kill him!
- Kill him!

1115
01:17:57,796 --> 01:17:58,671
Hey...!

1116
01:17:59,380 --> 01:18:00,255
Hey...!

1117
01:18:10,713 --> 01:18:12,838
They weren't my targets.
So I didn't strike.

1118
01:18:17,505 --> 01:18:18,380
Hey...!

1119
01:18:19,588 --> 01:18:21,838
He was my target.
That's why the bullet went through him.

1120
01:18:23,421 --> 01:18:25,421
How could you pull the trigger
on Miya Bhai?

1121
01:18:27,296 --> 01:18:28,755
- Bhai!
- Like this!

1122
01:18:30,713 --> 01:18:33,880
Hey! What gave you the nerve
to shoot him?

1123
01:18:35,255 --> 01:18:36,213
Bhai! Bhai!

1124
01:18:36,296 --> 01:18:37,963
- Bhai! Bhai!
- This did.

1125
01:18:38,213 --> 01:18:41,255
Hey! Shut your mouths, you fools!

1126
01:18:41,505 --> 01:18:44,380
Every time you speak,
he fires another round.

1127
01:18:49,255 --> 01:18:50,463
Hey! What's wrong with you?

1128
01:18:50,546 --> 01:18:52,046
Take one more step, and you're dead.

1129
01:18:52,505 --> 01:18:53,546
Sit, you idiot!

1130
01:18:58,005 --> 01:18:59,171
How does it feel, Miya?

1131
01:18:59,505 --> 01:19:01,171
Hurts, doesn't it?

1132
01:19:02,505 --> 01:19:04,088
As per my training,

1133
01:19:04,171 --> 01:19:06,838
I put three bullets
just inches from his heart.

1134
01:19:06,921 --> 01:19:09,463
He has 20 minutes.
Just 20 minutes.

1135
01:19:09,546 --> 01:19:12,421
Here's the deal. Hand him over to me
and take him back alive.

1136
01:19:12,505 --> 01:19:13,463
Hey!

1137
01:19:13,880 --> 01:19:17,838
Let's keep this professional.
A clean exchange. No chaos.

1138
01:19:19,130 --> 01:19:21,630
Why are you all hesitating?
I'm giving you a golden offer.

1139
01:19:21,796 --> 01:19:24,005
- So? Do we have a deal?
- Yeah, we do.

1140
01:19:24,088 --> 01:19:26,255
Good.
Get up, you moron!

1141
01:19:59,380 --> 01:20:03,005
Hey! What's this?
You were supposed to protect him.

1142
01:20:03,088 --> 01:20:05,338
Ugh! For the first time,
I saw fear in your eyes.

1143
01:20:05,421 --> 01:20:07,546
For the first time,
I met someone who even scared me.

1144
01:20:07,796 --> 01:20:09,921
He dragged away a terrorist
like he's some teddy bear.

1145
01:20:14,963 --> 01:20:19,255
If he doesn't come out,
we'll be exposed.

1146
01:20:20,505 --> 01:20:22,588
This time, you're not
going to the hospital.

1147
01:20:22,838 --> 01:20:24,505
Straight to...

1148
01:20:25,171 --> 01:20:27,046
We'll bring in
the Shiva Kashi brothers, sir.

1149
01:20:27,463 --> 01:20:28,671
I'll take care of it.

1150
01:20:29,338 --> 01:20:31,921
As instructed, we've set up
a 360-degree surveillance around Nagappa.

1151
01:20:32,171 --> 01:20:34,713
His entire crime network
operates from his hometown, Nallapadu.

1152
01:20:36,713 --> 01:20:37,838
NALLAPADU

1153
01:20:40,130 --> 01:20:41,005
It's true, sir.

1154
01:20:41,088 --> 01:20:44,630
The Thalam Butchaiah family
has been loyal to Nagappa for generations.

1155
01:20:44,755 --> 01:20:47,421
They're prepared
to kill or die for Nagappa, sir.

1156
01:20:48,171 --> 01:20:49,713
The bus reached the village.
Where are you, guys?

1157
01:20:49,796 --> 01:20:51,338
- On our way, bro.
- How much longer?

1158
01:20:51,421 --> 01:20:52,880
- We're close by.
- Hurry up, guys!

1159
01:20:52,963 --> 01:20:54,046
Don't step off the bus
until we come over.

1160
01:20:54,130 --> 01:20:55,546
Alright. I'll stay right here.

1161
01:21:00,088 --> 01:21:01,213
NO SMOKING

1162
01:21:01,296 --> 01:21:02,630
They're known as
Thaalam Shiva Kashi.

1163
01:21:03,921 --> 01:21:05,963
The brothers, Shiva and Kashi.

1164
01:21:06,505 --> 01:21:08,213
The Shiva Kashi brothers
are highly dangerous.

1165
01:21:08,380 --> 01:21:09,755
They're Nagappa's backbone.

1166
01:21:12,671 --> 01:21:14,421
Intelligence confirms
they're currently in Hyderabad.

1167
01:21:14,546 --> 01:21:16,713
Being Hindus,
they staged the attack

1168
01:21:16,796 --> 01:21:18,338
during the chariot procession
without suspicion.

1169
01:21:18,921 --> 01:21:21,671
They'll go to any extent
to free Ajmal Raheem.

1170
01:21:23,463 --> 01:21:25,046
Do you know
this nation's greatest tragedy?

1171
01:21:25,130 --> 01:21:27,130
Our people sing
other nations' praises.

1172
01:21:28,421 --> 01:21:30,463
This time,
we start the music, Kamal.

1173
01:21:30,838 --> 01:21:32,046
- Shoot them down!
- Sir?

1174
01:21:32,671 --> 01:21:34,546
Shoot them on sight!

1175
01:21:34,880 --> 01:21:36,213
"Hot desi.com."

1176
01:21:36,296 --> 01:21:40,171
"Hot news: Terrorist firing in Kashmir."

1177
01:21:40,255 --> 01:21:42,171
"Four soldiers dead."

1178
01:21:42,255 --> 01:21:44,338
Routine. What's new in this?

1179
01:21:44,421 --> 01:21:46,213
They knowingly went there and died.

1180
01:21:46,296 --> 01:21:48,921
You call this news?
What's this, bro?

1181
01:21:49,005 --> 01:21:49,963
Routine!

1182
01:21:50,588 --> 01:21:52,921
"Rupee drops again..."

1183
01:21:53,588 --> 01:21:55,421
You pushing it up.
Go lift it!

1184
01:21:55,671 --> 01:21:57,463
Routine! Next!

1185
01:21:57,880 --> 01:22:01,963
"Who's that heroine
in Salman Khan's farm the other day?"

1186
01:22:02,046 --> 01:22:03,713
This one! This one!

1187
01:22:03,796 --> 01:22:06,338
Save for later.
We can read during office hours, bro.

1188
01:22:07,713 --> 01:22:10,796
"We won't chant 'Bharat Mata ki Jai!'.
A bold statement by opposition."

1189
01:22:11,130 --> 01:22:12,963
Don't! We to won't say it.

1190
01:22:13,046 --> 01:22:15,296
Bharat mata!
Bharat mata! Bharat Mata!

1191
01:22:15,755 --> 01:22:18,755
What with this ruckus?
What do you say, bro?

1192
01:22:19,255 --> 01:22:20,421
You're always correct, bro.

1193
01:22:20,838 --> 01:22:22,713
Brothers, please don't talk ill
about the country.

1194
01:22:23,421 --> 01:22:24,296
Understood.

1195
01:22:24,963 --> 01:22:28,171
You came down here for a movie chance
from Amalapuram or Rajahmundry.

1196
01:22:29,046 --> 01:22:31,296
You haven't found
a single chance despite trying hard.

1197
01:22:31,380 --> 01:22:33,713
You don't go back to your village
fearing your prestige would be damaged.

1198
01:22:33,796 --> 01:22:36,005
Hello, we'll cover your travel fare.

1199
01:22:37,171 --> 01:22:38,296
Of course.

1200
01:22:40,380 --> 01:22:46,296
At Siachen, with a temperature of -40°C
they melt snow to drink water.

1201
01:22:46,713 --> 01:22:49,255
But you don't even care
when our soldiers die over there.

1202
01:22:49,338 --> 01:22:50,380
- No.
- Yeah. We don't.

1203
01:22:52,088 --> 01:22:53,796
- What's with the gun?
- Who the hell are you?

1204
01:22:53,921 --> 01:22:56,671
Making fun of the soldiers and army, eh?

1205
01:22:57,963 --> 01:23:01,255
While our soldiers put their life at risk
and conduct a surgical strike,

1206
01:23:01,338 --> 01:23:03,630
you sit here
and question it asking for proof.

1207
01:23:04,046 --> 01:23:05,380
You wanted proof?
Come. I'll give you.

1208
01:23:06,171 --> 01:23:09,296
What exactly is your problem to say
"Glory to Mother India!"

1209
01:23:09,380 --> 01:23:10,588
No, sir. Nothing.

1210
01:23:10,796 --> 01:23:12,963
- Glory to Mother India!
- Jai!

1211
01:23:13,046 --> 01:23:15,505
- Glory to Mother India!
- Jai! Jai!

1212
01:23:16,421 --> 01:23:17,963
What's with you?
Isn't this your country?

1213
01:23:18,046 --> 01:23:19,088
You too say it!

1214
01:23:19,171 --> 01:23:21,755
- Glory to Mother India!
- All Hail!

1215
01:23:21,838 --> 01:23:24,005
- Glory to Mother India!
- All Hail!

1216
01:23:24,088 --> 01:23:25,380
- Get lost!
- Sir! Sir!

1217
01:23:26,213 --> 01:23:27,755
Glory to Mother India!

1218
01:23:27,838 --> 01:23:29,046
Glory to Mother India!

1219
01:23:43,921 --> 01:23:47,296
It's just an RJ job.
Why are you drowning in books?

1220
01:23:48,088 --> 01:23:50,338
If you want to keep talking,
you need confidence.

1221
01:23:51,463 --> 01:23:54,796
To begin with, the name of our show
is "Gala Gala with Leela."

1222
01:23:55,213 --> 01:23:58,505
- Gapless gossips!
- Gold prices are soaring again?

1223
01:23:58,921 --> 01:24:01,588
I'm pure gold myself.
Who needs jewelry?

1224
01:24:02,421 --> 01:24:05,880
The coach says the team lost
because his wife brings bad luck.

1225
01:24:06,838 --> 01:24:10,005
This channel is just as useless.
Only Sreenu Swami gets it right.

1226
01:24:10,255 --> 01:24:14,213
A celebrity couple
will file a divorce this month.

1227
01:24:15,255 --> 01:24:17,630
Sir, could you tell us
what's in store for Virgo?

1228
01:24:18,088 --> 01:24:20,630
Virgos are in for an exceptional time!

1229
01:24:21,005 --> 01:24:22,713
Hey, that's your zodiac sign!

1230
01:24:24,505 --> 01:24:25,588
Absolute nonsense.

1231
01:24:26,005 --> 01:24:30,755
Today, fate will bring
your future husband across your path.

1232
01:24:31,046 --> 01:24:32,796
But how will she know
when he shows up?

1233
01:24:32,880 --> 01:24:34,088
How will she recognize him?

1234
01:24:34,380 --> 01:24:37,380
He'll walk right up to her,
place a bindi on her forehead.

1235
01:24:37,463 --> 01:24:39,130
Hey, he's talking about your future!

1236
01:24:39,213 --> 01:24:40,921
You're going to meet
your future husband today!

1237
01:24:41,005 --> 01:24:42,046
And if it doesn't come true?

1238
01:24:42,463 --> 01:24:44,921
I'll never wear bindi again. Ever.

1239
01:24:45,005 --> 01:24:46,796
You pay peanuts
and demand predictions.

1240
01:24:46,880 --> 01:24:49,130
What nonsense.
These things never come true.

1241
01:24:50,171 --> 01:24:52,755
My future husband, he says.
Coming from where, exactly?

1242
01:24:52,838 --> 01:24:55,338
I'm working from home today.
Have a nice day!

1243
01:25:05,046 --> 01:25:05,921
Give me tea.

1244
01:25:08,421 --> 01:25:09,463
- Yes, Kamal.
- Sir.

1245
01:25:09,713 --> 01:25:11,296
I've got Kashi sir,
one of the Shiva Kashi brothers.

1246
01:25:11,713 --> 01:25:13,880
- He's at Manja Market, sir.
- Take him down. I'm on my way.

1247
01:25:45,255 --> 01:25:46,213
Darn!

1248
01:25:55,630 --> 01:25:57,130
- Comb down the entire hostel.
- Yes, sir!

1249
01:25:57,213 --> 01:25:58,255
Okay, sir.
Okay, sir!

1250
01:25:58,380 --> 01:26:02,213
He hid at the I. S. Circle PG hostel
while making his escape, sir.

1251
01:26:04,421 --> 01:26:06,380
- The entire PG hostel is secured, sir.
- Good job, Kamal.

1252
01:26:07,296 --> 01:26:10,671
Shoot on sight. No hesitation.
We'll deal with the consequences later.

1253
01:26:10,755 --> 01:26:11,630
Okay, sir.

1254
01:26:12,505 --> 01:26:13,421
Pallavi!

1255
01:26:14,255 --> 01:26:16,088
Let's head out. Get ready, quickly!

1256
01:26:42,755 --> 01:26:44,546
A terror suspect has entered the hostel.

1257
01:26:44,630 --> 01:26:46,255
- Do not leave your room. Please get in.
- Okay, sir.

1258
01:26:49,963 --> 01:26:51,463
A terror suspect has entered the hostel.

1259
01:26:51,546 --> 01:26:52,838
- Please, be careful and lock the doors.
- Okay, sir.

1260
01:26:59,046 --> 01:26:59,963
Excuse me?

1261
01:27:04,796 --> 01:27:06,463
A terror suspect has escaped
and entered this area.

1262
01:27:06,546 --> 01:27:08,171
If you see anyone suspicious,
alert us immediately. Okay?

1263
01:27:08,255 --> 01:27:11,088
- Okay, sir.
- Just lock the door. Be inside.

1264
01:27:12,046 --> 01:27:12,963
Yes, sir.

1265
01:27:16,088 --> 01:27:17,046
Pallavi!

1266
01:27:19,755 --> 01:27:21,171
- Is everything alright?
- Huh?

1267
01:27:21,755 --> 01:27:22,713
I'm talking to you.

1268
01:27:23,296 --> 01:27:24,546
I'm talking to you.
Are you okay?

1269
01:27:26,296 --> 01:27:27,963
If anyone looks suspicious, call me.

1270
01:27:28,046 --> 01:27:29,005
Please take my number.

1271
01:27:30,880 --> 01:27:32,463
Okay, sir.
Okay.

1272
01:27:33,921 --> 01:27:35,921
93924 18602

1273
01:27:53,463 --> 01:27:54,421
Give that to me.

1274
01:27:55,171 --> 01:27:59,005
- Please, sir leave my friend!
- Your friend is getting me out of here.

1275
01:28:14,463 --> 01:28:15,921
Take this phone and recover the data.

1276
01:28:23,546 --> 01:28:25,213
Good job, Miss...

1277
01:28:26,213 --> 01:28:27,130
Leela.

1278
01:28:27,213 --> 01:28:28,963
- Thank you so much. Thank you!
- Thank you...

1279
01:28:31,796 --> 01:28:32,713
This bindi...

1280
01:28:33,963 --> 01:28:35,380
would look far better
on your forehead.

1281
01:28:36,130 --> 01:28:38,546
Go on, take it.
It'll look beautiful on you.

1282
01:28:46,255 --> 01:28:48,213
Now you look better.
Beautiful.

1283
01:28:49,546 --> 01:28:50,421
Bye!

1284
01:28:52,130 --> 01:28:55,713
You're going to meet
your future husband today!

1285
01:28:56,421 --> 01:28:59,963
He'll walk right up to her,
place a bindi on her forehead.

1286
01:29:00,130 --> 01:29:01,088
How...?

1287
01:29:03,213 --> 01:29:04,130
What are you guys doing here?

1288
01:29:06,296 --> 01:29:07,255
What brings you here?

1289
01:29:09,005 --> 01:29:09,963
Any problem?

1290
01:29:10,213 --> 01:29:11,755
There's been a mistake yesterday...

1291
01:29:12,046 --> 01:29:13,296
A small mistake.

1292
01:29:14,213 --> 01:29:15,088
Please, tell me.

1293
01:29:15,171 --> 01:29:18,630
Yesterday's show made me out
to be some kind of hero.

1294
01:29:18,796 --> 01:29:20,588
Overnight, I became a star.

1295
01:29:20,796 --> 01:29:22,880
I let it get to my head...

1296
01:29:23,130 --> 01:29:25,421
Terror suspect apprehended
at a PG hostel.

1297
01:29:25,505 --> 01:29:26,546
That's our top story.

1298
01:29:26,671 --> 01:29:29,588
And I was the one who made it happen.
That's the real story. Yes!

1299
01:29:29,838 --> 01:29:35,088
ACP Bhagat received the tip-off
from none other than your own RJ Leela.

1300
01:29:35,171 --> 01:29:36,296
Leela, Leela.

1301
01:29:36,380 --> 01:29:40,046
Leela isn't just gossip and giggles,
she's got real guts. Real courage.

1302
01:29:40,130 --> 01:29:41,255
Hey, Kashi!

1303
01:29:41,338 --> 01:29:43,588
That's my hostel.
This is my studio.

1304
01:29:43,671 --> 01:29:46,088
And this is my open challenge to you.

1305
01:29:46,171 --> 01:29:48,130
A woman isn't fragile, you moron.

1306
01:29:48,213 --> 01:29:50,921
She's a war drum.
And when she beats, it resounds.

1307
01:29:51,005 --> 01:29:52,046
And with that same fire,

1308
01:29:52,130 --> 01:29:54,171
that same electric energy
from the film Kushi,

1309
01:29:54,255 --> 01:29:58,630
this one goes out to all of you!
"Ye mera jaha, tera kaam kya hai yaha"

1310
01:29:58,713 --> 01:30:00,630
This is my turf

1311
01:30:00,838 --> 01:30:03,255
This is my home... my abode

1312
01:30:03,380 --> 01:30:05,463
This is my world

1313
01:30:05,713 --> 01:30:08,130
What's your business here?

1314
01:30:09,671 --> 01:30:12,005
Hello and welcome to Gala Gala with Leela!

1315
01:30:12,088 --> 01:30:14,588
- What would you like to hear today?
- Your last breath.

1316
01:30:14,838 --> 01:30:15,755
What?!

1317
01:30:17,046 --> 01:30:21,088
Today is Friday.
Before my man walks into court on Monday,

1318
01:30:21,255 --> 01:30:22,421
you'll already be dead.

1319
01:30:22,963 --> 01:30:24,463
I will put you in the ground.

1320
01:30:25,296 --> 01:30:27,046
Go running to whoever's backing you.

1321
01:30:28,088 --> 01:30:29,046
Hey, Kashi!

1322
01:30:29,130 --> 01:30:31,380
That's my hostel! This is my studio!

1323
01:30:31,463 --> 01:30:33,796
And this is my open challenge to you!

1324
01:30:35,755 --> 01:30:37,713
Well, aren't you something!

1325
01:30:40,005 --> 01:30:41,005
Ms. Leela!

1326
01:30:42,046 --> 01:30:44,630
- You know what's beautiful about you?
- I have no idea, sir.

1327
01:30:44,713 --> 01:30:45,713
It's your madness.

1328
01:30:46,713 --> 01:30:47,755
The madness within you.

1329
01:30:47,838 --> 01:30:50,130
- Why do you say that, sir?
- Then what?

1330
01:30:50,671 --> 01:30:52,921
When you speak with enthusiasm,
you'll earn compliments.

1331
01:30:53,005 --> 01:30:55,671
But when you speak carelessly,
you invite complications.

1332
01:30:57,046 --> 01:31:00,046
You took all the credit
and let the whole team down.

1333
01:31:00,130 --> 01:31:01,088
That's fine.

1334
01:31:01,255 --> 01:31:03,921
But couldn't you see
you crossed the line with him?

1335
01:31:05,463 --> 01:31:06,838
Try using your own head for once.

1336
01:31:07,380 --> 01:31:10,005
You sent three words
and act like you stopped World War III.

1337
01:31:10,088 --> 01:31:11,921
Blowing into a mic,
chasing clout around town.

1338
01:31:12,671 --> 01:31:14,255
That's what your friend does.

1339
01:31:14,338 --> 01:31:16,463
What if you set the convict free?

1340
01:31:17,046 --> 01:31:18,671
He'll finish you off
and stroll right out of here.

1341
01:31:19,755 --> 01:31:21,171
- Leela!
- What now?

1342
01:31:22,130 --> 01:31:24,171
It's okay.
At least we can catch him with this.

1343
01:31:25,088 --> 01:31:27,088
Don't worry, miss. I've got you.

1344
01:31:27,171 --> 01:31:29,421
But you won't be with me all 24 hours.

1345
01:31:29,505 --> 01:31:30,421
Not just 24 hours.

1346
01:31:30,505 --> 01:31:33,671
I'll stay by your side
for the full 72, just like he said.

1347
01:31:35,630 --> 01:31:38,213
As long as our boss is with you,
no harm will come your way.

1348
01:31:38,296 --> 01:31:40,546
Mr. Reddy, ease up on the theatrics.

1349
01:31:41,380 --> 01:31:44,005
Don't put yourself at risk
just for the sake of a good line.

1350
01:31:49,088 --> 01:31:51,171
This is my turf

1351
01:31:53,713 --> 01:31:56,255
This is my home... my abode

1352
01:31:58,630 --> 01:32:03,130
This is my world
What's your business here?

1353
01:32:03,213 --> 01:32:05,005
Hello, Hyderabad!

1354
01:32:05,088 --> 01:32:08,046
I'm here with lots of chatter
and a pile of gossip.

1355
01:32:08,130 --> 01:32:10,796
Welcome to Gala Gala with Leela.

1356
01:32:16,588 --> 01:32:17,505
Thank you.

1357
01:32:24,546 --> 01:32:25,463
Why are you staring at?

1358
01:32:25,546 --> 01:32:27,921
Protection program means we should be
looking after you, not you at us.

1359
01:32:28,296 --> 01:32:32,963
- My heart hums for you
- Hi, Leela!

1360
01:32:33,046 --> 01:32:36,963
My heart sings for you

1361
01:32:37,505 --> 01:32:39,630
What happened, babe?

1362
01:32:39,963 --> 01:32:42,421
He's bothering me by coming here.

1363
01:32:44,130 --> 01:32:46,505
He's singing exactly
what I feel too, babe.

1364
01:32:47,755 --> 01:32:49,505
What do you think I should do, babe?

1365
01:32:56,213 --> 01:32:58,421
Listen, Leela,
Mr. Bhagat is visiting daily.

1366
01:32:58,505 --> 01:32:59,755
Why can't you grab an interview with him?

1367
01:33:00,130 --> 01:33:01,296
That's a good idea.

1368
01:33:01,546 --> 01:33:03,463
- Please, Leela!
- Sure, sir!

1369
01:33:04,546 --> 01:33:07,588
I have a lot of questions to ask.

1370
01:33:10,338 --> 01:33:12,671
I'm feeling good today

1371
01:33:14,921 --> 01:33:17,255
Nothing's going to get in my way

1372
01:33:18,255 --> 01:33:20,630
I'm grateful you brought me
to the pub right when I asked, sir.

1373
01:33:22,255 --> 01:33:24,255
Here, no one can notice the folks,
and no noise can be heard.

1374
01:33:24,630 --> 01:33:26,755
I hope he comes to finish you off.

1375
01:33:26,838 --> 01:33:29,130
- Mr. Bhagat!
- Okay!

1376
01:33:29,213 --> 01:33:30,921
You enjoy, and we'll stay on duty.

1377
01:33:31,588 --> 01:33:33,338
- Can I get you something?
- Sure!

1378
01:33:34,255 --> 01:33:36,171
A glass of water and peace of mind.

1379
01:33:37,005 --> 01:33:38,130
Great!

1380
01:33:41,088 --> 01:33:42,505
Looks like he won't join us, guys.

1381
01:33:45,005 --> 01:33:46,005
Lovely weather, isn't it?

1382
01:33:46,088 --> 01:33:49,838
- My heart hums for you
- Leela?

1383
01:33:50,546 --> 01:33:51,963
What happened again, babe?

1384
01:33:52,046 --> 01:33:56,255
It's the same.
He's singing exactly what I feel too.

1385
01:33:58,380 --> 01:34:00,588
I'm dying inside, seriously!

1386
01:34:02,838 --> 01:34:04,421
Hello, Hyderabad!

1387
01:34:04,588 --> 01:34:07,255
Guess who's with us today?

1388
01:34:07,380 --> 01:34:12,505
The one and only
dashing and dynamic Bhagat! Bhagat...

1389
01:34:12,588 --> 01:34:13,588
Me?

1390
01:34:14,005 --> 01:34:15,005
And dashing, eh?

1391
01:34:15,505 --> 01:34:19,713
In your line of duty,
how is your job satisfaction?

1392
01:34:20,463 --> 01:34:21,921
A woman blesses me,

1393
01:34:22,963 --> 01:34:25,171
hand on my head.

1394
01:34:25,796 --> 01:34:28,005
A sister says,
"You brought courage in me, brother."

1395
01:34:28,671 --> 01:34:31,713
I take this as luck
and an opportunity from God.

1396
01:34:33,380 --> 01:34:34,796
I'm not doing anyone a favor.

1397
01:34:35,338 --> 01:34:36,713
I'm doing my duty.

1398
01:34:38,046 --> 01:34:39,630
Everyone gains wealth,

1399
01:34:40,213 --> 01:34:43,421
yet only a few gain blessings.

1400
01:34:44,046 --> 01:34:45,296
Truly inspiring.

1401
01:34:47,838 --> 01:34:50,671
We're going deep into the matter,
so, next question.

1402
01:34:51,505 --> 01:34:56,796
Tell us, what do you feel
when a beautiful lady passes by?

1403
01:34:58,963 --> 01:35:00,130
Lots of feelings, Miss!

1404
01:35:00,463 --> 01:35:03,130
Did you hear that?

1405
01:35:03,505 --> 01:35:06,713
Mr. Bhagat is slowly
sharing his thoughts.

1406
01:35:06,796 --> 01:35:08,505
Tell us what do you feel?

1407
01:35:08,588 --> 01:35:12,588
I mean,
I wish troublemakers don't chase her.

1408
01:35:13,838 --> 01:35:17,463
If she's ever chased,
I wish she'd know self-defense techniques.

1409
01:35:19,005 --> 01:35:22,338
I wish she reaches home safely.

1410
01:35:22,713 --> 01:35:24,421
How bad do you think they days are?

1411
01:35:24,838 --> 01:35:27,421
If every girl reaches her home,
then who comes to yours?

1412
01:35:28,296 --> 01:35:31,796
I mean, you must have someone
in your life, right, sir?

1413
01:35:32,505 --> 01:35:33,463
I have one.

1414
01:35:34,130 --> 01:35:35,505
My darling, my sweetheart.

1415
01:35:35,921 --> 01:35:37,255
Who's that sweetheart?

1416
01:35:39,130 --> 01:35:40,338
Here is my heartbeat!

1417
01:35:41,796 --> 01:35:44,588
Look at the conture and shape!

1418
01:35:45,380 --> 01:35:46,921
Who wouldn't fall
in love with this?

1419
01:35:47,130 --> 01:35:49,505
Fine, then go and live with it.

1420
01:35:51,755 --> 01:35:54,546
You've been burning with rage.
How did you calm off, babe?

1421
01:35:54,796 --> 01:35:59,338
Babe, don't know why,
but magic happens on his comeback.

1422
01:36:18,880 --> 01:36:23,588
My heart hums for you

1423
01:36:23,671 --> 01:36:28,713
My heart sings for you

1424
01:36:29,338 --> 01:36:33,880
It keeps running toward you
Begging you to hear its whispers

1425
01:36:34,463 --> 01:36:38,546
Like rising waves, it grows restless
Because it sees you within itself

1426
01:36:40,463 --> 01:36:45,213
My heart hums for you

1427
01:36:45,296 --> 01:36:50,630
My heart sings for you

1428
01:37:24,880 --> 01:37:29,421
A maiden who has seen many dreams
Can no longer sleep in peace

1429
01:37:29,630 --> 01:37:34,171
She realizes you are
The first light she was searching for

1430
01:37:34,255 --> 01:37:38,880
A maiden who has seen many dreams
Can no longer sleep in peace

1431
01:37:39,296 --> 01:37:43,505
She realizes you are
the first light she was searching for

1432
01:37:44,130 --> 01:37:48,838
Even after reaching
The shore it longed for

1433
01:37:48,921 --> 01:37:53,046
Why does this longing still remain?

1434
01:37:53,380 --> 01:37:55,463
It keeps circling behind you
Refusing to let go of its beloved

1435
01:37:55,546 --> 01:37:58,255
Even with the blessing it received
It cannot stand still in calm

1436
01:37:58,421 --> 01:38:02,921
What would soothe it?
It waits to hear the answer

1437
01:38:04,380 --> 01:38:09,171
My heart hums for you

1438
01:38:09,255 --> 01:38:14,796
My heart sings for you

1439
01:39:00,880 --> 01:39:05,463
It cherishes your companionship
And admires the beauty in you

1440
01:39:05,713 --> 01:39:10,421
Yet still it asks for more
A desire that never ends

1441
01:39:10,505 --> 01:39:15,005
It cherishes your companionship
And admires the beauty in you

1442
01:39:15,296 --> 01:39:20,046
Yet still it asks for more
A desire that never ends

1443
01:39:20,171 --> 01:39:24,838
Your friendship flows like a flood
And wraps around me

1444
01:39:24,921 --> 01:39:29,046
Your moonlit smile
Leaves my heart moist with emotion

1445
01:39:29,380 --> 01:39:31,671
This longing never fades
This restlessness never quiets

1446
01:39:31,755 --> 01:39:34,171
It never admits
That this madness is for you

1447
01:39:34,463 --> 01:39:40,130
What would bring it peace?
Do you know what it longs for?

1448
01:39:40,505 --> 01:39:45,171
My heart hums for you

1449
01:39:45,255 --> 01:39:50,421
My heart sings for you

1450
01:39:50,838 --> 01:39:55,630
It keeps running toward you
Begging you to hear its whispers

1451
01:39:56,088 --> 01:40:00,380
Like rising waves, it grows restless
Because it sees you within itself

1452
01:40:02,088 --> 01:40:06,796
My heart hums for you

1453
01:40:06,880 --> 01:40:12,588
My heart sings for you

1454
01:40:21,380 --> 01:40:23,296
Did you come all this way
just to buy bangles?

1455
01:40:23,671 --> 01:40:26,171
Your boss insisted good bangles

1456
01:40:26,255 --> 01:40:28,755
are found in Chudi Bazaar,
not in fancy malls.

1457
01:40:28,880 --> 01:40:29,838
Where is he?

1458
01:40:29,963 --> 01:40:32,380
He's in a meeting with
the Chief Minister. He'll be back soon.

1459
01:40:32,463 --> 01:40:36,463
On day one, he brought ten men
in a jeep for my "protection."

1460
01:40:36,713 --> 01:40:38,921
Day two, it became four.

1461
01:40:39,130 --> 01:40:40,713
And today, it's just you in this auto.

1462
01:40:40,838 --> 01:40:41,838
Are you upset

1463
01:40:41,921 --> 01:40:44,505
because there's no security
or because he's not here?

1464
01:40:46,130 --> 01:40:47,505
I don't need protection.

1465
01:40:47,588 --> 01:40:48,921
I can handle myself.

1466
01:40:49,338 --> 01:40:50,255
Ma'am, ma'am!

1467
01:40:50,338 --> 01:40:51,671
- Please wait, ma'am.
- Security, he says.

1468
01:40:51,755 --> 01:40:54,171
- Sir, sir!
- Police!

1469
01:41:47,796 --> 01:41:52,380
Doesn't spring itself come

1470
01:41:52,546 --> 01:41:57,046
To forests that cannot reach it?

1471
01:41:58,088 --> 01:42:02,588
Doesn't spring itself come

1472
01:42:02,838 --> 01:42:07,880
To forests that cannot reach it?

1473
01:42:11,546 --> 01:42:14,046
I took Leela to pubs and clubs.
You didn't come.

1474
01:42:14,671 --> 01:42:16,796
I roamed malls in a topless jeep.

1475
01:42:17,421 --> 01:42:18,588
But you still didn't come.

1476
01:42:19,338 --> 01:42:20,880
There's a song I loved as a child.

1477
01:42:22,005 --> 01:42:25,671
When the forests couldn't reach Spring,
Spring went to them.

1478
01:42:26,921 --> 01:42:30,005
If you weren't coming for Leela.
That's why I made her come to you.

1479
01:42:31,130 --> 01:42:32,046
Wow!

1480
01:42:32,296 --> 01:42:33,671
These are but my divine plays.

1481
01:42:35,130 --> 01:42:37,713
That's why this operation is called,
"Humming while hunting."

1482
01:42:38,171 --> 01:42:39,171
Hope you like it.

1483
01:42:39,880 --> 01:42:41,296
Mr. Sastry, thank you.

1484
01:42:41,880 --> 01:42:44,171
You made me use Telugu literature
to speak to criminals.

1485
01:42:45,380 --> 01:42:46,338
Hey!

1486
01:42:46,963 --> 01:42:50,005
My groundwork is rock solid,
and my network's next level.

1487
01:42:52,838 --> 01:42:54,880
Boys! Say goodbye to the target.

1488
01:43:05,296 --> 01:43:08,546
If we fire the last shot,
the high is on another level.

1489
01:43:12,796 --> 01:43:17,005
Doesn't spring itself come

1490
01:43:17,171 --> 01:43:21,338
To forests that cannot reach it?

1491
01:43:22,296 --> 01:43:26,463
Doesn't spring itself come

1492
01:43:26,630 --> 01:43:31,171
To forests that cannot reach it?

1493
01:43:31,880 --> 01:43:32,755
Thank you, everyone.

1494
01:43:32,838 --> 01:43:34,630
Why did he get caught so quickly?

1495
01:43:34,921 --> 01:43:36,171
Couldn't he stay hidden a little longer?

1496
01:43:36,755 --> 01:43:38,796
Rascal! He got caught in just three days.

1497
01:43:39,130 --> 01:43:41,088
Three days? It took longer than that.

1498
01:43:41,421 --> 01:43:42,338
Leela...

1499
01:43:42,421 --> 01:43:44,838
This chase began
with Leela's bindi in a PG...

1500
01:43:44,921 --> 01:43:46,338
and ended with bangles in Chudi Bazaar.

1501
01:43:50,505 --> 01:43:53,588
Aren't criminals and terrorists
supposed to be ruthless?

1502
01:43:54,130 --> 01:43:56,213
How do he get caught
shopping for bangles?

1503
01:43:56,296 --> 01:43:59,005
Congratulations, Ms. Leela. You've proven
not only can a woman help a man's victory

1504
01:43:59,088 --> 01:44:01,963
but also in nabbing criminals.

1505
01:44:02,380 --> 01:44:04,505
- Take care. Bye, see you soon.
- When?

1506
01:44:06,546 --> 01:44:08,296
Well... You did say "soon."

1507
01:44:08,380 --> 01:44:09,463
So... when exactly?

1508
01:44:09,546 --> 01:44:11,088
Whenever you're in trouble.

1509
01:44:11,171 --> 01:44:14,338
If any of you ever run into trouble,
tell them you belong to Bhagat.

1510
01:44:14,671 --> 01:44:16,588
If that doesn't work, come to me.
Alright?

1511
01:44:32,421 --> 01:44:36,255
Just in. Nallapadu crime mafia's
Shiva Kashi brothers

1512
01:44:36,338 --> 01:44:40,171
were killed in an encounter
by ACP Bhagat while escaping custody.

1513
01:44:44,088 --> 01:44:45,588
Hey, this mongrel!

1514
01:44:53,005 --> 01:44:53,880
What happened?

1515
01:44:54,213 --> 01:44:56,755
He encountered the Shiva Kashi brothers.

1516
01:44:58,005 --> 01:44:59,713
Wasn't he afraid of you?

1517
01:45:00,671 --> 01:45:02,255
Or does he fear no one?

1518
01:45:03,463 --> 01:45:04,713
He fears no one.

1519
01:45:06,255 --> 01:45:08,463
If we can make a fearless man afraid...

1520
01:45:09,838 --> 01:45:11,713
we can scare anyone.

1521
01:45:12,046 --> 01:45:13,796
If we had finished him at the station,
this wouldn't have happened.

1522
01:45:14,338 --> 01:45:16,546
I don't want him dead.

1523
01:45:17,088 --> 01:45:18,296
I want him trembling in fear.

1524
01:45:19,505 --> 01:45:20,421
What's the plan?

1525
01:45:27,546 --> 01:45:29,171
What's your Seenu Swamy saying lately?

1526
01:45:29,421 --> 01:45:31,130
He says you should confess
your feelings first.

1527
01:45:39,921 --> 01:45:41,713
You're here again?
What happened this time?

1528
01:45:42,046 --> 01:45:43,546
I got into trouble.

1529
01:45:44,046 --> 01:45:45,588
Since the electricity bill's too high,

1530
01:45:45,671 --> 01:45:49,005
they're cutting the power
at the PG after 10 p. m.

1531
01:45:51,838 --> 01:45:53,421
Aspiring collectors

1532
01:45:53,505 --> 01:45:56,171
- must now study under streetlights and--
- That's enough.

1533
01:45:56,463 --> 01:45:57,796
- Mr. Reddy!
- Sir.

1534
01:45:57,880 --> 01:46:00,130
- Handle her current affairs.
- As you say, sir.

1535
01:46:02,046 --> 01:46:05,796
At this rate,
her "tensions" will blow our fuses too.

1536
01:46:07,838 --> 01:46:09,796
What is it now? Water problem?

1537
01:46:11,463 --> 01:46:12,338
I thought as much.

1538
01:46:12,421 --> 01:46:14,380
- Mr. Reddy!
- I'm here. I'm here!

1539
01:46:14,505 --> 01:46:15,796
We're ready, sir.

1540
01:46:24,630 --> 01:46:28,255
What's with your scratching?
Are your hands itching or what?

1541
01:46:29,630 --> 01:46:31,963
- Do you even know who I am?
- No idea.

1542
01:46:32,338 --> 01:46:34,546
This quiet heart of mine
is dying to know you.

1543
01:46:34,630 --> 01:46:37,130
We all belong to ACP Bhagat.

1544
01:46:37,213 --> 01:46:41,213
Oh God! Forgive me, sister.
I'm truly sorry. Please!

1545
01:46:41,838 --> 01:46:45,171
Desperate, my foot!
His fuses are blown now.

1546
01:46:45,255 --> 01:46:46,463
Pull over!

1547
01:46:47,963 --> 01:46:50,588
What's all this roadside drama, ma'am?

1548
01:46:50,671 --> 01:46:53,630
No number plate. No helmet.
Still not afraid of us?

1549
01:46:53,713 --> 01:46:55,005
- Hello!
- Yes!

1550
01:46:55,088 --> 01:46:56,380
Do you know who we belong to?

1551
01:46:56,463 --> 01:46:57,796
Why would we care
about your personal life?

1552
01:46:57,880 --> 01:47:00,005
It belongs to Mr. ACP Bhagat.

1553
01:47:02,046 --> 01:47:03,296
What is it now?

1554
01:47:03,755 --> 01:47:07,546
When I asked for extra onions,
the pani puri vendor picked a fight.

1555
01:47:07,630 --> 01:47:08,505
These days,

1556
01:47:08,588 --> 01:47:11,671
- this is every youngster's struggle--
- Mr. Reddy!

1557
01:47:12,380 --> 01:47:14,505
He's already headed
to the pani puri stall.

1558
01:47:15,296 --> 01:47:16,296
Thanks.

1559
01:47:16,380 --> 01:47:19,546
Yes! He's the one!
Lock him up and take action!

1560
01:47:19,880 --> 01:47:21,838
- Step out. Now.
- Sir.

1561
01:47:21,963 --> 01:47:25,171
We're stuck here suffering
because you refused her extra onions?

1562
01:47:25,296 --> 01:47:27,921
Do you even know who she is?
She belongs to ACP Bhagat.

1563
01:47:28,171 --> 01:47:31,838
If she had told me sooner,
I'd have handed over the whole stall.

1564
01:47:31,963 --> 01:47:33,005
You're on the right track now.

1565
01:47:37,296 --> 01:47:39,171
- Hello?
- Where are you?

1566
01:47:39,588 --> 01:47:41,130
- Who are you?
- Who am I?

1567
01:47:41,213 --> 01:47:42,213
I own you!

1568
01:47:42,296 --> 01:47:44,671
Think about what will happen to you
after listening to me.

1569
01:47:44,755 --> 01:47:46,171
You're flirting with girls from the PG

1570
01:47:46,255 --> 01:47:48,046
when you're supposed
to be doing your duty?

1571
01:47:48,213 --> 01:47:52,713
Just because she was with you,
she'll be on her deathbed in minutes.

1572
01:47:52,880 --> 01:47:53,755
Hey!

1573
01:47:55,130 --> 01:47:57,171
Go. Say your final goodbye.

1574
01:47:57,963 --> 01:47:59,005
There's no time!

1575
01:47:59,380 --> 01:48:00,880
Run! Run, you mongrel!

1576
01:48:01,338 --> 01:48:02,463
Hey, start the vehicle!

1577
01:48:06,505 --> 01:48:08,963
Sir, where did the rape happen?
Who's responsible?

1578
01:48:09,046 --> 01:48:11,088
- Any information, sir?
- Sir, sir.

1579
01:48:11,338 --> 01:48:12,421
Sir, sir.

1580
01:48:12,505 --> 01:48:15,463
We were starving for breaking news,
and now we've got a rape case, sir!

1581
01:48:15,546 --> 01:48:16,463
- Why are you stopping us, sir?
- Sir, sir.

1582
01:48:16,546 --> 01:48:17,838
We need a sound bite
while she's still alive, right?

1583
01:48:17,921 --> 01:48:19,421
Otherwise we'll have to make do
with the post-mortem report.

1584
01:48:19,505 --> 01:48:20,713
- Yes, sir.
- Sir, I'm talking to you.

1585
01:48:20,796 --> 01:48:21,671
Say something, sir.

1586
01:48:21,838 --> 01:48:23,671
- Police tyranny!
- Must end!

1587
01:48:23,755 --> 01:48:25,838
- Long live!
- Press freedom!

1588
01:48:26,838 --> 01:48:29,005
Leela! Leela...

1589
01:48:30,588 --> 01:48:31,671
Pallavi...

1590
01:48:33,338 --> 01:48:34,296
Pallavi.

1591
01:48:35,380 --> 01:48:36,255
Sir.

1592
01:48:36,338 --> 01:48:37,796
Since they shared a room,

1593
01:48:38,130 --> 01:48:41,380
the men who came for Leela
took Pallavi instead.

1594
01:48:53,755 --> 01:48:54,838
She was raped.

1595
01:48:56,005 --> 01:48:59,005
Brutally and repeatedly.

1596
01:48:59,713 --> 01:49:01,671
They tortured her brutally.

1597
01:49:03,755 --> 01:49:05,005
Heavy blood loss!

1598
01:49:05,505 --> 01:49:07,380
Her intestines are critically damaged.

1599
01:49:09,296 --> 01:49:10,755
To destroy forensic evidence,

1600
01:49:11,755 --> 01:49:13,671
they used a rusted rod and...

1601
01:49:42,630 --> 01:49:45,463
At a time like this,
even talking to you feels wrong.

1602
01:49:46,505 --> 01:49:49,630
Forcing you to talk feels even worse.

1603
01:49:55,255 --> 01:49:56,255
Listen to me, Pallavi.

1604
01:49:57,963 --> 01:49:58,921
Not as a police...

1605
01:50:00,296 --> 01:50:01,463
But I'm asking you as a brother.

1606
01:50:03,338 --> 01:50:04,713
Tell me what happened.

1607
01:50:06,380 --> 01:50:08,046
Four monsters, brother.

1608
01:50:15,963 --> 01:50:17,630
Please let me go.

1609
01:50:22,630 --> 01:50:26,880
I realized later
they were actually looking for Leela.

1610
01:50:29,880 --> 01:50:32,963
Hey! Isn't your boyfriend a cop?

1611
01:50:33,421 --> 01:50:34,296
Call him now!

1612
01:50:34,380 --> 01:50:35,463
Call that mongrel!

1613
01:50:41,963 --> 01:50:43,505
If I had told them the truth,

1614
01:50:43,755 --> 01:50:47,463
Leela would've been here instead of me.

1615
01:50:47,546 --> 01:50:49,921
So I endured it... brother.

1616
01:51:00,546 --> 01:51:03,713
They gagged me with cloth

1617
01:51:03,963 --> 01:51:07,171
so my screams wouldn't destroy their mood.

1618
01:51:20,671 --> 01:51:23,796
They took turns,
trying to outdo each other,

1619
01:51:23,880 --> 01:51:26,338
while assaulting me through the night.

1620
01:51:33,588 --> 01:51:34,671
Hey.

1621
01:51:44,213 --> 01:51:49,546
For the first time,
I hated being born a woman.

1622
01:52:00,130 --> 01:52:03,838
You asked what I wanted
for Raksha Bandhan, remember?

1623
01:52:06,338 --> 01:52:09,421
I want the dead bodies
of those sons of mongrels!

1624
01:52:09,671 --> 01:52:10,838
I want them dead!

1625
01:52:16,130 --> 01:52:18,338
- Hey, camera!
- Sir, sir.

1626
01:52:18,421 --> 01:52:19,630
Sir, sir!

1627
01:52:19,796 --> 01:52:22,255
Was it really a rape
or did she consent with...

1628
01:52:23,171 --> 01:52:26,463
No cop is there before a crime happens.
But once it happens, everyone plays hero.

1629
01:52:27,880 --> 01:52:29,671
The girl's situation is critical.

1630
01:52:30,421 --> 01:52:33,463
Right now, a moment of silence
is all we can give her.

1631
01:52:35,338 --> 01:52:38,671
It's been a slow news week, sir.
Give us something.

1632
01:52:39,005 --> 01:52:39,880
Sir.

1633
01:52:41,088 --> 01:52:43,213
- You want sensational news, right?
- Yes, sir.

1634
01:52:43,463 --> 01:52:46,796
I'll give you something twice
as explosive within 24 hours.

1635
01:52:46,880 --> 01:52:49,005
What's that sensational news, sir?
Please tell us.

1636
01:52:49,088 --> 01:52:52,088
- Give us a hint, sir.
- Tell us, sir. What is it?

1637
01:52:56,588 --> 01:52:57,713
Hey, SP!

1638
01:52:57,880 --> 01:53:02,546
I don't understand if he is born to me
or me to him because of his deeds.

1639
01:53:02,880 --> 01:53:04,755
Look at his sneaky laugh.

1640
01:53:10,213 --> 01:53:12,338
- You're absolutely right.
- Good night, sir.

1641
01:53:14,546 --> 01:53:15,463
I pity you.

1642
01:53:16,255 --> 01:53:17,213
Can't help.

1643
01:53:23,546 --> 01:53:27,255
You're under arrest in Pallavi's case.
If you move, I'll encounter you.

1644
01:53:32,671 --> 01:53:35,838
He's not going anywhere.
I guarantee it.

1645
01:53:36,380 --> 01:53:39,838
Read this first.
It'll shake you to your core.

1646
01:53:47,838 --> 01:53:51,130
A warrant isn't enough to arrest my man.

1647
01:53:52,796 --> 01:53:54,838
You need your badge intact first.

1648
01:53:55,338 --> 01:53:57,338
- How's that line?
- Brilliant, Dad.

1649
01:54:04,005 --> 01:54:06,963
All that arrogance comes
from that uniform, doesn't it?

1650
01:54:08,171 --> 01:54:11,338
That's why I suspended you,
and stripped you of it.

1651
01:54:14,671 --> 01:54:15,588
Get lost!

1652
01:54:21,588 --> 01:54:23,505
I heard she's not your girlfriend.

1653
01:54:24,380 --> 01:54:27,338
The SP said she was her friend.

1654
01:54:30,421 --> 01:54:32,505
She entertained them well.

1655
01:54:34,213 --> 01:54:37,171
Ugh! He's my son.
I shouldn't speak about it.

1656
01:54:37,380 --> 01:54:38,755
Let him tell it himself.

1657
01:54:39,213 --> 01:54:40,671
Go on, son.

1658
01:54:41,713 --> 01:54:43,880
Ugh! Stop it, Dad.
You're too much.

1659
01:54:44,005 --> 01:54:45,630
She's a total hottie!

1660
01:54:45,713 --> 01:54:49,588
Every inch of her demanded attention.

1661
01:54:50,755 --> 01:54:53,046
Let me go! Let me go!

1662
01:54:55,005 --> 01:54:56,046
Please let me go!

1663
01:54:59,171 --> 01:55:02,213
Whether it's food or pleasure,
I've always shared with my friends.

1664
01:55:02,296 --> 01:55:04,255
That's why, we all...

1665
01:55:05,505 --> 01:55:06,796
That's enough, son.

1666
01:55:06,880 --> 01:55:08,546
He seems upset.

1667
01:55:10,505 --> 01:55:12,213
But from now on,
you should be afraid.

1668
01:55:12,546 --> 01:55:13,713
This doesn't end here!

1669
01:55:14,046 --> 01:55:18,338
You should be scared if your girlfriend
doesn't call or pick up.

1670
01:55:18,463 --> 01:55:20,380
You should be terrified!

1671
01:55:20,463 --> 01:55:21,505
You should!

1672
01:55:22,296 --> 01:55:23,421
After the wedding,

1673
01:55:23,505 --> 01:55:26,546
you won't live with your wife.
You'll live in fear.

1674
01:55:28,463 --> 01:55:32,213
First your wife. Then your mother.
Then your sister, if you have one.

1675
01:55:32,296 --> 01:55:36,171
Forget your family.
I'll kill anyone who cares about you.

1676
01:55:36,755 --> 01:55:39,796
This is my roadmap for the future.

1677
01:55:55,421 --> 01:55:56,671
This is what fear means.

1678
01:55:57,921 --> 01:55:59,255
And this how courage looks like.

1679
01:56:03,463 --> 01:56:07,171
Every time I meet people like you,
this uniform holds me back.

1680
01:56:07,255 --> 01:56:08,213
Thank you, Mr.Nagappa.

1681
01:56:10,588 --> 01:56:12,171
You removed the restraints.
The gates are wide open now.

1682
01:56:13,630 --> 01:56:14,588
Hey, Nagappa!

1683
01:56:15,380 --> 01:56:16,838
In uniform,
I'm limited to one weapon.

1684
01:56:17,213 --> 01:56:22,963
Now I can kill you with whatever I find.
Be it a rod, a stone, or a blade!

1685
01:56:24,880 --> 01:56:26,505
See? Like this.

1686
01:56:27,755 --> 01:56:31,046
I've got unlimited choices!
Unlimited choices!

1687
01:56:32,588 --> 01:56:35,338
Don't go around saying
Bhagat took the law into his own hands.

1688
01:56:36,213 --> 01:56:38,255
Say he unsheathed his sword.

1689
01:56:38,630 --> 01:56:39,755
Tell them he plunged it in!

1690
01:56:48,588 --> 01:56:52,630
Everyone you care about and everyone
who cares about you will be killed.

1691
01:56:54,255 --> 01:56:57,005
Hey! What were you saying?

1692
01:56:58,463 --> 01:57:00,796
You want to kill those who care about me?

1693
01:57:01,755 --> 01:57:04,880
Do you even know how many there are?

1694
01:57:06,213 --> 01:57:09,505
You'd need a lifetime to count them,
let alone touch them.

1695
01:57:10,671 --> 01:57:11,630
Give it a try!

1696
01:57:12,671 --> 01:57:13,546
Do it!

1697
01:57:18,005 --> 01:57:19,171
Give it a try!

1698
01:57:44,046 --> 01:57:45,005
Tell me now.

1699
01:57:45,505 --> 01:57:46,505
Is what I did wrong?

1700
01:57:46,630 --> 01:57:48,296
It's not you who was wrong.
It's my bloody dad!

1701
01:57:48,546 --> 01:57:50,921
He watched his own son
who proved his "manhood" get killed.

1702
01:57:51,213 --> 01:57:53,588
But he told me it was a heart attack
since I was in the U. S.

1703
01:57:54,088 --> 01:57:56,296
After everything you've heard,

1704
01:57:56,755 --> 01:58:00,463
instead of calling your brother a monster,
you're talking about "manhood"?

1705
01:58:02,171 --> 01:58:03,130
Filthy rat!

1706
01:58:03,255 --> 01:58:04,213
Manhood?

1707
01:58:04,713 --> 01:58:07,005
You provoked a man as calm as the ocean.

1708
01:58:07,088 --> 01:58:10,338
That's why you're facing a tsunami.
And this is only the beginning.

1709
01:58:13,588 --> 01:58:15,005
What happened next?

1710
01:58:15,963 --> 01:58:16,963
Justice!

1711
01:58:20,213 --> 01:58:21,380
Justice was served.

1712
01:58:53,046 --> 01:58:54,963
I can console you all I want,
but I can't ease your pain.

1713
01:58:56,130 --> 01:58:57,630
But I understand it.

1714
01:58:57,755 --> 01:58:59,005
Pallavi's dead, sir.

1715
01:59:00,463 --> 01:59:01,755
But her memories...

1716
01:59:06,796 --> 01:59:09,296
Hey, call Leela.
Let's three go out.

1717
01:59:09,671 --> 01:59:10,713
Leela left, sir.

1718
01:59:12,963 --> 01:59:13,880
Where to?

1719
01:59:14,213 --> 01:59:17,296
She couldn't adjust to this city.
She couldn't bear the people here.

1720
01:59:18,296 --> 01:59:20,380
She moved back to her village
to live with her grandfather.

1721
01:59:24,880 --> 01:59:26,505
Come in, sir.
Please be seated.

1722
01:59:28,338 --> 01:59:29,505
Let me get you some water.

1723
01:59:29,588 --> 01:59:31,213
I'm Leela's grandpa.

1724
01:59:31,296 --> 01:59:33,421
- Come on. Please sit.
- Greetings.

1725
01:59:34,671 --> 01:59:36,671
Hey! Sit over here. On the chair.

1726
01:59:42,380 --> 01:59:44,296
Leela's situation is not looking good.

1727
01:59:45,088 --> 01:59:47,505
She doesn't eat.
She doesn't speak either.

1728
01:59:47,630 --> 01:59:49,213
She wakes up terrified at night.

1729
01:59:49,338 --> 01:59:50,755
When I ask why, she just cries.

1730
01:59:50,963 --> 01:59:52,296
I'm here for her now...

1731
01:59:53,130 --> 01:59:54,463
but what if I'm gone tomorrow?

1732
01:59:56,255 --> 01:59:58,296
She has no one else.

1733
02:00:03,338 --> 02:00:05,505
Call Leela once. I'll talk to her.

1734
02:00:05,880 --> 02:00:06,796
Sir.

1735
02:00:13,005 --> 02:00:13,921
Grandpa!

1736
02:00:14,963 --> 02:00:16,338
Where have you been since morning?

1737
02:00:17,171 --> 02:00:18,796
Where do I search for you?

1738
02:00:19,838 --> 02:00:22,255
- You didn't even tell me--
- Your grandfather's safe.

1739
02:00:26,755 --> 02:00:28,630
Grandpa's phone... why is it with you?

1740
02:00:28,755 --> 02:00:31,005
He came to town to buy fertilizer.
We happened to cross paths.

1741
02:00:32,088 --> 02:00:34,713
He's anxious about living alone
after you get married.

1742
02:00:37,880 --> 02:00:40,630
By the way... after we're married,
will Grandpa live with us?

1743
02:00:41,005 --> 02:00:42,963
Of course! Grandpa always lives with me...

1744
02:00:52,546 --> 02:00:55,963
I mean... after we're married,
will he stay with us?

1745
02:01:01,130 --> 02:01:02,421
Tell me, Leela. I'm asking you.

1746
02:01:02,713 --> 02:01:05,005
Grandpa and I are waiting for your answer.

1747
02:01:10,338 --> 02:01:12,421
- Yes.
- Were you frightened by what happened?

1748
02:01:14,963 --> 02:01:15,963
Why fear?

1749
02:01:17,255 --> 02:01:18,296
I'm here, aren't I?

1750
02:01:23,005 --> 02:01:25,338
Ms. Leela... tell me, who are you?

1751
02:01:27,380 --> 02:01:28,921
I belong to Bhagat.

1752
02:01:29,088 --> 02:01:30,213
That's how it is!

1753
02:01:30,463 --> 02:01:32,630
We have an IPS officers' gathering
this evening.

1754
02:01:32,880 --> 02:01:34,380
I'd like to introduce you.
Will you join me?

1755
02:02:13,713 --> 02:02:16,255
Rum pum pum
Rum pum pum

1756
02:02:18,588 --> 02:02:21,255
One step and the ground shakes

1757
02:02:23,630 --> 02:02:26,213
Dham dham dham
Feel the rhythm

1758
02:02:28,546 --> 02:02:31,421
Let's storm the floor
Like a raging wind

1759
02:02:33,463 --> 02:02:35,755
Even if the Bay of Bengal rises

1760
02:02:35,838 --> 02:02:38,296
Even if the ray of hope fades

1761
02:02:38,380 --> 02:02:40,713
Even if life turns into a tug-of-war

1762
02:02:40,796 --> 02:02:43,255
Even if takeoff is late

1763
02:02:43,338 --> 02:02:48,088
We'll face it, man
We've seen worse

1764
02:02:52,755 --> 02:02:57,838
We'll face it, man
We've seen worse

1765
02:03:22,088 --> 02:03:27,046
The space on your lips
Is meant for a smile

1766
02:03:27,296 --> 02:03:31,671
Let a new you rise from within
Feel your heart leap within

1767
02:03:31,880 --> 02:03:36,755
The ground beneath your feet
Belongs to you. Believe it

1768
02:03:37,046 --> 02:03:41,546
Dance free like a carefree peacock
Let the world echo with your moves

1769
02:03:42,005 --> 02:03:44,421
Even if arrows come out of nowhere

1770
02:03:44,505 --> 02:03:46,880
Even if narrow minds
Try to hold you down

1771
02:03:46,963 --> 02:03:49,171
Even if a shallow sea
Tries to drown you

1772
02:03:49,255 --> 02:03:51,838
Tomorrow will still play on our side

1773
02:03:51,921 --> 02:03:56,755
We'll face it, man
We've seen worse

1774
02:04:01,296 --> 02:04:06,546
We'll face it, man
We've seen worse

1775
02:04:40,505 --> 02:04:44,796
My heart beat suddenly races faster

1776
02:04:45,671 --> 02:04:50,546
Like a spark igniting inside
Those fiery eyes spin my world around

1777
02:04:50,630 --> 02:04:54,421
A whistle song
Floats into the flower garden

1778
02:04:55,505 --> 02:05:00,338
Something sends a shiver down my spine
If shy glances start sending signals

1779
02:05:00,421 --> 02:05:05,088
Let the problems stand in a queue
Put up a board "No Entry"

1780
02:05:05,296 --> 02:05:09,963
Let's throw them out without mercy
What do we lose if we fight?

1781
02:05:10,380 --> 02:05:15,046
We'll face it, man
We've seen worse

1782
02:05:19,671 --> 02:05:24,921
We'll face it, man
We've seen worse

1783
02:05:34,380 --> 02:05:36,546
- Grab those flowers.
- Sure, master.

1784
02:05:37,671 --> 02:05:38,880
Stay blessed, my dear.

1785
02:05:44,880 --> 02:05:48,588
With heart and word in harmony

1786
02:05:48,963 --> 02:05:52,463
At her lotus feet
Love begins to bloom

1787
02:05:52,546 --> 02:05:56,546
Beloved maiden, soft in her smile
With a face like the gentle moon

1788
02:05:56,630 --> 02:06:02,005
Virtuous, with lotus-like eyes
A beauty blessed in every way

1789
02:06:02,088 --> 02:06:04,005
- Greetings, sir.
- Greetings.

1790
02:06:04,088 --> 02:06:05,713
Why hold the ceremony
all the way out here?

1791
02:06:05,796 --> 02:06:07,630
- The bride insisted on getting married
- Hi, Mr. CM!

1792
02:06:07,713 --> 02:06:08,713
at her grandfather's house.

1793
02:06:08,796 --> 02:06:09,713
Oh, okay.

1794
02:06:09,880 --> 02:06:11,505
- Greetings, sir.
- Greetings.

1795
02:06:14,505 --> 02:06:16,213
Hey, wait a second.

1796
02:06:16,671 --> 02:06:18,671
Do I look like I'm heading
to a political rally?

1797
02:06:18,838 --> 02:06:20,546
- It's a family wedding.
- Okay, sir.

1798
02:06:20,630 --> 02:06:23,088
- You don't even let me pee in peace.
- Greetings, CM sir.

1799
02:06:23,421 --> 02:06:25,296
- Greetings. How have you been?
- I'm good, sir.

1800
02:06:26,505 --> 02:06:29,130
Hey, please sit.
You're the groom, after all.

1801
02:06:29,213 --> 02:06:30,755
- You shouldn't get up.
- Greetings, sir.

1802
02:06:31,463 --> 02:06:32,546
Greetings.

1803
02:06:33,380 --> 02:06:34,713
You both look great together.

1804
02:06:35,296 --> 02:06:36,505
Sir, please.

1805
02:06:36,588 --> 02:06:37,630
It's alright.

1806
02:06:40,755 --> 02:06:44,880
May they always live in happiness
Blessed as a couple for all time

1807
02:06:44,963 --> 02:06:48,755
This sacred union of marriage
Becomes the very meaning of my life

1808
02:06:48,838 --> 02:06:52,838
May they always live in happiness
Blessed as a couple for all time

1809
02:06:52,921 --> 02:06:56,713
This sacred union of marriage
Becomes the very meaning of my life

1810
02:07:06,421 --> 02:07:07,380
Leela, dear!

1811
02:07:19,463 --> 02:07:20,463
Sir! Sir!

1812
02:07:27,796 --> 02:07:29,380
Sir, let's go. Please, sir.

1813
02:07:29,796 --> 02:07:32,421
- Sir, please come.
- Come here.

1814
02:07:44,713 --> 02:07:45,796
Move! Fast!

1815
02:07:45,880 --> 02:07:47,796
- Don't worry, sir.
- Is Bhagat alright?

1816
02:07:49,296 --> 02:07:51,671
- Bhagat!
- Move!

1817
02:07:54,171 --> 02:07:56,171
- Start the car, now.
- Tak-- take care of Bhagat.

1818
02:08:43,838 --> 02:08:45,546
What a mess, son!

1819
02:08:46,755 --> 02:08:47,963
Even the enemy should not...

1820
02:08:49,255 --> 02:08:50,255
By the way...

1821
02:08:51,380 --> 02:08:53,046
you are my enemy right?

1822
02:08:54,255 --> 02:08:56,046
Then what happened was justified.

1823
02:08:56,380 --> 02:09:00,630
Your bad luck is that
not one bullet missed your people.

1824
02:09:00,838 --> 02:09:04,505
And your good luck is you weren't hit.

1825
02:09:04,921 --> 02:09:06,171
I instructed it must not hit.

1826
02:09:08,838 --> 02:09:10,796
If I use a bullet,
you'll be dead in 10 seconds

1827
02:09:11,338 --> 02:09:13,463
But I've used my brain,

1828
02:09:14,005 --> 02:09:15,713
and every moment will kill you.

1829
02:09:16,880 --> 02:09:19,671
You have to stay alive
to endure the pain

1830
02:09:19,755 --> 02:09:23,130
of your love ones
being killed in front of you.

1831
02:09:25,588 --> 02:09:27,005
You must be alive

1832
02:09:27,088 --> 02:09:31,755
to witness the master on his deathbed
the one who taught you calculations.

1833
02:09:32,880 --> 02:09:35,255
I, Chadhala Marri Nalla Nagappa!

1834
02:09:35,338 --> 02:09:36,963
Me! Myself!

1835
02:09:37,463 --> 02:09:39,463
while performing the oath-taking ceremony

1836
02:09:39,880 --> 02:09:43,463
you must live to witness it.

1837
02:09:46,380 --> 02:09:47,963
You killed my elder son, right?

1838
02:09:48,921 --> 02:09:49,963
That's fine.

1839
02:09:50,505 --> 02:09:55,296
That's when
I brought my second son into this world.

1840
02:09:55,880 --> 02:10:00,546
He's arriving from America right now.

1841
02:10:01,088 --> 02:10:02,838
Now it's my turn, next my son's turn.

1842
02:10:02,963 --> 02:10:03,921
And it's our rule.

1843
02:10:05,505 --> 02:10:07,796
You walked on my photo that day.

1844
02:10:10,130 --> 02:10:12,255
Tomorrow, you must witness

1845
02:10:12,505 --> 02:10:15,588
everyone bowing
to my photo in every office.

1846
02:10:16,713 --> 02:10:18,130
You are a righteous one.

1847
02:10:18,213 --> 02:10:20,463
If you die, you go straight to heaven.

1848
02:10:20,546 --> 02:10:23,838
To experience hell, you must live.

1849
02:10:24,505 --> 02:10:26,296
Nagappa, you've made a grave mistake.

1850
02:10:26,630 --> 02:10:29,630
Do you mean killing your family?

1851
02:10:29,796 --> 02:10:31,421
No! Sparing my life.

1852
02:10:37,130 --> 02:10:40,171
Got the guts?
Strip me of power and authority.

1853
02:10:42,796 --> 02:10:44,171
May you live long!

1854
02:10:46,796 --> 02:10:48,213
You must be alive.

1855
02:10:59,088 --> 02:11:00,963
Your health is in critical condition.

1856
02:11:01,963 --> 02:11:03,963
The doctors advise
moving you to Singapore.

1857
02:11:04,130 --> 02:11:07,380
Listen, only if you promise me
to leave the city,

1858
02:11:07,713 --> 02:11:11,130
I'll go to Singapore and get treatment.

1859
02:11:11,796 --> 02:11:13,838
The Bhagavad Gita was spoken in
the middle of a war, sir.

1860
02:11:15,505 --> 02:11:17,505
It never said to abandon the war halfway.

1861
02:11:17,588 --> 02:11:20,755
I'm too weak to convince you.

1862
02:11:21,171 --> 02:11:23,213
My boy,
if you don't leave,

1863
02:11:24,296 --> 02:11:25,380
I too won't.

1864
02:11:26,338 --> 02:11:29,838
Promise me you'll leave the city.

1865
02:11:30,880 --> 02:11:35,880
I don't agree with you leaving
following the old man's words, Bhagat.

1866
02:11:36,046 --> 02:11:40,296
Sir, I understand
Nagappa's grudge against me.

1867
02:11:41,630 --> 02:11:44,921
Rather than the goons and hired killers,

1868
02:11:45,130 --> 02:11:48,213
bringing in Afzal Baghdadi,
who runs an international terror network.

1869
02:11:48,588 --> 02:11:49,630
Point of concern, sir.

1870
02:11:54,713 --> 02:11:57,755
Sir, during Ajmal Rahim's remand,
many truths came to light, sir.

1871
02:12:03,463 --> 02:12:06,796
An intelligence report revealed
they run terror training camps

1872
02:12:06,880 --> 02:12:09,546
in the Nallamala Forest, sir.

1873
02:12:10,755 --> 02:12:11,963
Allahu akbar!
Allahu akbar!

1874
02:12:12,213 --> 02:12:14,505
I have a team who work for me.

1875
02:12:14,630 --> 02:12:16,880
They're trustworthy,
of course, from our department.

1876
02:12:16,963 --> 02:12:19,588
- Sir, I need your help, when required.
- Sure.

1877
02:12:19,755 --> 02:12:21,588
I'll show them
how it's like when I go to the forest.

1878
02:12:22,921 --> 02:12:25,838
I don't spray the leaves.
I poison the roots.

1879
02:12:28,921 --> 02:12:31,921
I'm shedding the uniform,
not the war, sir.

1880
02:12:35,046 --> 02:12:37,921
His war isn't personal.
It's for society.

1881
02:12:41,588 --> 02:12:45,671
So tell me, was your father wrong or not?

1882
02:12:46,255 --> 02:12:49,880
Yes! Letting you live
that day was a mistake.

1883
02:12:50,130 --> 02:12:52,963
That damn old man let his ego
run wild and he challenged you

1884
02:12:53,713 --> 02:12:54,713
See...

1885
02:12:55,005 --> 02:12:57,088
I told you everything in detail,

1886
02:12:57,380 --> 02:13:01,046
instead of recognizing
your dad as a cruel man,

1887
02:13:02,171 --> 02:13:04,213
still clung
to your pride and your rage.

1888
02:13:09,088 --> 02:13:10,046
And you?

1889
02:13:10,880 --> 02:13:12,880
You've been staring at me
from the moment you came.

1890
02:13:13,588 --> 02:13:15,963
What exactly
is running in your head? Huh?

1891
02:13:16,088 --> 02:13:19,380
I myself haven't met Baghdadi till today.
How do you think you could?

1892
02:13:19,463 --> 02:13:21,755
If he doesn't come, this guy's finished.

1893
02:13:22,130 --> 02:13:24,255
I've shared the location
with your Miya Bhai.

1894
02:13:25,296 --> 02:13:28,880
Baghdadi will surely come here.
and die right here.

1895
02:13:41,546 --> 02:13:42,838
You're going to have it now.

1896
02:13:45,380 --> 02:13:46,921
Where the hell is Baghdadi?

1897
02:13:57,296 --> 02:13:59,130
Best wishes, Ustaad,

1898
02:14:00,130 --> 02:14:01,130
I'm finally here.

1899
02:14:02,755 --> 02:14:03,796
I'm Baghdadi.

1900
02:14:05,171 --> 02:14:06,546
And I'm a total radical.

1901
02:14:09,255 --> 02:14:12,380
So you're wondering how Nagappa is
linked to a terrorist like me?

1902
02:14:13,296 --> 02:14:15,213
Our mission is the same.

1903
02:14:15,838 --> 02:14:17,171
It is to alter the demographics.

1904
02:14:17,255 --> 02:14:19,421
- What should I do now?
- Treason.

1905
02:14:19,505 --> 02:14:21,380
- And my gain?
- Power.

1906
02:14:22,838 --> 02:14:25,838
We land a lakh of people from
across the Bangladesh border

1907
02:14:28,255 --> 02:14:30,421
into your country annually.

1908
02:14:37,213 --> 02:14:39,588
Nagappa will provide them with Voter IDs.

1909
02:14:41,005 --> 02:14:44,463
They give Nagappa their votes.
He hands out Aadhaar cards.

1910
02:14:46,338 --> 02:14:48,338
Nagappa will rise to power.

1911
02:14:49,505 --> 02:14:55,130
We're not using ammo, but population
to wage this war on you.

1912
02:14:56,963 --> 02:14:59,921
I marked your wife with vermilion
before you ever did.

1913
02:15:00,630 --> 02:15:02,630
How do you like my Sindoor?

1914
02:15:10,255 --> 02:15:11,880
Only your Guru remains now.

1915
02:15:12,713 --> 02:15:16,130
He's returning to be
sworn in as CM again.

1916
02:15:19,505 --> 02:15:21,380
Your real enemies aren't us!

1917
02:15:21,463 --> 02:15:23,421
There are more than
enough of them in your own land.

1918
02:15:23,505 --> 02:15:25,588
And they're about to
take the ex-CM down!

1919
02:15:28,671 --> 02:15:30,963
Son, Faisal, you did a great job.

1920
02:15:31,713 --> 02:15:35,421
You tracked the CM's son and made sure
Ustaad brought him straight to us.

1921
02:15:35,630 --> 02:15:37,088
What reward do you want?

1922
02:15:37,713 --> 02:15:40,630
I want this entire operation to be
carried out by my hands!

1923
02:15:40,713 --> 02:15:42,755
These hands alone must kill him.

1924
02:15:43,130 --> 02:15:46,505
- Inshallah!
- Finish him, Faisal!

1925
02:15:48,505 --> 02:15:52,005
Bravo! It'll take you two hours
just to cross that forest.

1926
02:15:52,088 --> 02:15:54,171
You won't even get a
final glimpse of the CM.

1927
02:15:58,671 --> 02:16:00,838
I'm going to activate
one by one from right here.

1928
02:16:01,296 --> 02:16:02,171
Nayeem!

1929
02:16:08,588 --> 02:16:11,005
Senior Z-Security
Chief Anand Rao Activate!

1930
02:16:12,005 --> 02:16:15,463
- Z-Security chief, Anand Rao activated.
- Copy, sir.

1931
02:16:19,005 --> 02:16:21,296
Activate First Chief Secretary
Veera Swamy!

1932
02:16:21,380 --> 02:16:22,255
Copy, sir.

1933
02:16:30,005 --> 02:16:32,338
Activate Assistant Intelligence Chief,
Ratnakar!

1934
02:16:32,421 --> 02:16:33,463
Activated.

1935
02:16:35,171 --> 02:16:37,213
Activate MLA Satya Prakash!

1936
02:16:41,463 --> 02:16:43,046
This guy has a massive following.

1937
02:16:45,005 --> 02:16:46,796
Whatever he does goes viral.

1938
02:16:48,505 --> 02:16:52,463
What happens to him goes viral now.

1939
02:17:05,421 --> 02:17:08,505
I, Chandra Sekhar Rao,

1940
02:17:08,588 --> 02:17:12,296
in the name of the Indian Constitution,

1941
02:17:12,421 --> 02:17:14,421
I swear in the name of god
to show true loyalty and obedience

1942
02:17:16,088 --> 02:17:17,671
You didn't come to the oath ceremony.

1943
02:17:17,755 --> 02:17:19,046
Where were you all these days?

1944
02:17:19,213 --> 02:17:21,213
You were the one who told
me to go into exile, sir.

1945
02:17:21,755 --> 02:17:23,838
I stayed there and started a
‘Clean and Green' program.

1946
02:17:24,380 --> 02:17:25,255
What do you mean?

1947
02:17:25,338 --> 02:17:27,588
To grow good plants, you have to
remove the weeds, sir.

1948
02:17:28,921 --> 02:17:29,880
That's what I did.

1949
02:17:30,005 --> 02:17:31,671
- Alright.
- I'll take your leave, sir.

1950
02:17:33,005 --> 02:17:36,296
What did you do with Nagappa?

1951
02:17:40,005 --> 02:17:45,963
You don't need credit for it,
but I need clarity.

1952
02:17:46,130 --> 02:17:49,630
I started the Clean and Green
program with Nagappa, sir.

1953
02:17:50,213 --> 02:17:52,171
Bhagavad Gita was told
during war, sir.

1954
02:17:52,671 --> 02:17:54,755
Never advised leaving midway.

1955
02:18:00,213 --> 02:18:02,588
Expose this to the media,

1956
02:18:03,463 --> 02:18:04,921
and you'll rot in Tihar Jail.

1957
02:18:09,963 --> 02:18:12,255
He shouts ‘Jai Hind' all the time.

1958
02:18:12,963 --> 02:18:16,755
I'll drill two full magazines
into his brain.

1959
02:18:17,255 --> 02:18:20,505
Let's see if he still says "Jai Hind."

1960
02:18:22,421 --> 02:18:25,380
All you'll hear from us is 'Jai Hind'!

1961
02:18:26,796 --> 02:18:28,338
I'll make your people say it, too.

1962
02:18:29,880 --> 02:18:30,796
Ready to listen?

1963
02:18:31,255 --> 02:18:33,546
- Ready to hear it?
- Go ahead.

1964
02:18:34,046 --> 02:18:36,671
- Try getting just one to say it.
- Listen closely.

1965
02:18:45,130 --> 02:18:46,505
Jai Hind!

1966
02:18:51,838 --> 02:18:53,546
This is Faisal Hussaini,
AKA Riaz Khan.

1967
02:18:53,630 --> 02:18:56,005
Reporting from undercover
special ops, Sir!

1968
02:19:01,630 --> 02:19:05,755
Riaz Khan, you topped the Civil
Services. Why choose IPS over IAS?

1969
02:19:06,088 --> 02:19:07,255
I followed your footsteps, Sir.

1970
02:19:07,338 --> 02:19:09,630
I am a huge, huge fan of your work, sir!

1971
02:19:17,213 --> 02:19:20,088
If you go to jail
you'll be a hero to some.

1972
02:19:20,505 --> 02:19:21,755
Or even role model.

1973
02:19:22,963 --> 02:19:25,296
Sadly, we live in a country
where criminals like Afzal Guru

1974
02:19:25,880 --> 02:19:27,380
and Yakub Memon have been glorified.

1975
02:19:33,671 --> 02:19:35,921
Your resume fit the mission perfectly.

1976
02:19:36,005 --> 02:19:38,130
I didn't activate your men.

1977
02:19:38,213 --> 02:19:39,130
I activated mine!

1978
02:19:42,921 --> 02:19:44,005
MLA Satya Prakash.

1979
02:19:51,755 --> 02:19:52,630
One.

1980
02:19:53,838 --> 02:19:54,713
Copy, sir.

1981
02:19:55,588 --> 02:19:56,463
Two.

1982
02:19:59,171 --> 02:20:00,255
I told you, didn't I?

1983
02:20:00,838 --> 02:20:02,088
My groundwork is rock solid.

1984
02:20:02,171 --> 02:20:03,880
And my network?
It's on a whole different level!

1985
02:20:17,213 --> 02:20:19,505
While I was plotting to kill you,

1986
02:20:20,296 --> 02:20:24,338
your 'best friend' sent a return gift.

1987
02:20:30,005 --> 02:20:33,463
If a beggar like you is this bold,

1988
02:20:33,630 --> 02:20:37,588
imagine the fire in us!
Can you?

1989
02:20:49,588 --> 02:20:51,630
Concentrated potassium cyanide.

1990
02:20:52,255 --> 02:20:53,921
The moment it touches your tongue,

1991
02:20:55,713 --> 02:20:57,088
you'll be out of everyone's touch.

1992
02:20:58,171 --> 02:21:00,130
Cardiac arrest in 90 seconds.

1993
02:21:01,880 --> 02:21:07,963
You live off scraps of charity,
yet you boast about wars and bloodshed.

1994
02:21:08,046 --> 02:21:09,505
This time, it won't be on streets.

1995
02:21:09,588 --> 02:21:10,921
We'll barge into your homes and kill you.

1996
02:21:17,380 --> 02:21:18,296
What was that you said?

1997
02:21:18,463 --> 02:21:19,421
What was it?

1998
02:21:19,713 --> 02:21:21,130
Baghdadi? A radical?

1999
02:21:21,755 --> 02:21:22,630
My name is Bhagat.

2000
02:21:23,546 --> 02:21:26,296
And I'm a pure-blooded Hindustani!
Hindustani!

2001
02:21:26,380 --> 02:21:28,796
And what else did you say?
What was it?

2002
02:21:32,255 --> 02:21:33,338
Sindhoor!

2003
02:21:34,838 --> 02:21:35,796
Sindhoor!

2004
02:21:39,796 --> 02:21:42,255
Our culture honors
every guest with a Tilak.

2005
02:21:43,713 --> 02:21:45,338
You've seen our women
do it with grace.

2006
02:21:47,421 --> 02:21:50,755
Now, see what happens
when a man applies it.

2007
02:21:51,755 --> 02:21:55,671
Watch how a man of
this land marks your end.

2008
02:21:57,005 --> 02:21:58,171
Do you want to see?

2009
02:22:46,505 --> 02:22:48,171
Your strength and your army...

2010
02:22:48,255 --> 02:22:53,838
Your own sons and your friends
across the border are all gone.

2011
02:22:59,796 --> 02:23:01,005
Once you're dead,
you're going to hell.

2012
02:23:01,921 --> 02:23:03,380
Want to feel hell while
you're still alive?

2013
02:23:05,880 --> 02:23:06,963
Choice is yours.

2014
02:23:35,380 --> 02:23:37,088
- Bhagat.
- Yes, sir.

2015
02:23:38,963 --> 02:23:42,713
Remember the promise you made as a child?

2016
02:23:43,505 --> 02:23:47,088
Promise me you'd be there
whenever I called.

2017
02:23:47,588 --> 02:23:51,005
Swear you'll dedicate
your life to the people.

2018
02:23:54,088 --> 02:23:56,005
Just as the sky has no end...

2019
02:23:59,338 --> 02:24:00,880
and the Earth has no borders...

2020
02:24:04,255 --> 02:24:09,546
your service must go beyond one
police station or one town.

2021
02:24:12,171 --> 02:24:15,005
Don't limit your service to a few.

2022
02:24:19,963 --> 02:24:21,505
At the end of the day,
I'm just a soldier, sir.

2023
02:24:22,671 --> 02:24:24,088
Not just a soldier.

2024
02:24:24,171 --> 02:24:28,171
A traveling soldier.
Yes! You're a traveling soldier.
